title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Lay the chicken in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the chicken is done and the water is absorbed.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, then let cool. Add the remainder of ingredients. Toss and serve.
Add the seasoning to taste.

title: elaine's famous peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and corn syrup.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla and beat until thick.
Add walnuts.
Pour into buttered platter.

title: donald nixon's bachelor beans
directions: Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes; stir twice.

title: italian pilgrims casserole
directions: Mix 6 tablespoons of ground almonds and about 2 tablespoons of margarine into the pumpkin.
Beat eggs and mix them with 2/3 of Parmesan cheese.
Gradually add pumpkin mixture to combine. Grease large baking dish with spray.
Pour mixture in dish and sprinkle with the remaining almonds and cheese.
Dot with the remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; set aside.
Saute green pepper, carrots and onion with sauerkraut until hot.
Pour into baking dish and put pork chops on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until pork chops are tender.

title: pecan pralines ii
directions: Measure 1 cup sugar in a black, iron or heavy aluminum pot and caramelize.
At the same time, bring milk and remaining 2 cups of sugar to a boil in saucepan.
Add milk mixture to caramelized sugar and cook together about 2 minutes.
(Be careful when adding milk to caramel as mixture bubbles up.)
Remove from fire.
Add 1/2 stick butter and beat until melted.
Add 2 to 3 cups pecans. Continue beating until thick and ready to drop.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: rose strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in wine, strawberries and undrained pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into an 8-cup mold; refrigerate until set.
Spread sour cream over top.
Spoon or carefully pour remaining gelatin mixture over top.
Refrigerate until set.
Unmold onto salad greens.
Serves 10.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown the hamburger, bacon and onion and drain.
Add brown sugar, sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder and pepper and mix.
Add the 4 kinds of beans and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook overnight in crock-pot.

title: orange marinade sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine salt, cornstarch and orange juice; stir to dissolve.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cook over medium-high heat about 1 minute until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in oil, garlic and oregano.
Let cool.
Use to marinate pork or duck before and during cooking.
Makes 1 cup.

title: piccadilly pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Garnish with circles of bell pepper or pimento.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a cookie sheet, then bake and cool. Top with a mixture of cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Top with glaze and fresh fruits.

title: chili boat
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut a slice from top of loaf to make a lid.
Hollow out loaf, reserving crumbs and leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Brush inside and out with melted butter.
Mix 1 cup reserved crumbs with celery, onion and chili in medium bowl. Spoon into loaf and sprinkle with cheese.
Replace top of bread. Wrap loaf in foil and place on baking sheet.
Bake 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: low calorie vegetable dip
directions: In a small bowl or blender, combine all ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Place in casserole dish. Crush chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: *You can use bars or blocks of white chocolate, coarsely chopped.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; shape in ball.

title: lemon gold cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add
baking
powder and sift together 3 times.
Cream
butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, small amounts at
a
time. Beat
after
each
addition
until
smooth.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans 25 to 30 minutes in moderate
oven
at
Spread with Lemon Frosting.
Double recipe to make 3 (10-inch) layers.

title: gulliver's corn au gratin
directions: Cook corn in very small amount of water. Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cream and simmer for 5 minutes with salt and Accent; add to creamed corn as thickened.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese, dot with butter and brown under broiler.

title: baked mostaccioli and chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts; leave whole.
Boil noodles; drain. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of noodles. Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken and noodles.
Spread cheese over sauce (thick).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is fully melted, then eat and enjoy.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix beaten eggs, flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add cheese, onion and spinach and mix well.
Put butter in baking pan (9 x 13-inch) and put in oven for a minute to melt and spread in pan.
Spread mixture into pan and level.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes before cutting.

title: corn flake balls
directions: Pour corn flakes into large bowl.
Put the peanut butter on top of flakes.
Mix syrup and sugar together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 45 seconds.
(If you cook it longer, it will become too hard.)
Quickly pour syrup mixture over corn flakes and peanut butter.
Stir rapidly; put a spoonful at a time in your hand to form a ball.
Put balls on wax paper to cool.

title: red raspberry pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with half of pie dough; refrigerate.
In large mixing bowl, blend together flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add raspberries and combine gently.
Pile filling into chilled pie shell.
Drizzle with lemon juice and dot with butter.
Cover with remaining dough; seal and crimp edges decoratively.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: mushroom lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream with drained, cooked ground beef. Add mushrooms to this. Bring water to a boil and cook noodles until tender.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer noodles, meat mixture and cheeses.
Bake at 375° until the cheese melts throughout.

title: pork chops and raisins
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides. Add hot water to pork chops, enough to cover.
Let cook approximately 1 hour.
About the last 20 minutes of cooking, add raisins. Cover and finish cooking.

title: old fashion sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.	Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into
a
large greased pan.
Cook for 45 minutes or until pudding turns slightly dark.
Stir often.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze water from spinach.
Combine with sour cream and vegetable soup.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours. Spoon-scoop bread from middle of bread to form a bread bowl. Serve dip with bread cubes and crackers.

title: peanut clusters(microwave)
directions: In an extra-large microwave-safe dish, mix sugar, syrup and water.
Stir well and microwave 3 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts and cook on High 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and food coloring and mix well.
Let cool somewhat and add butter.
Beat with a wooden spoon until thick.

title: orange-pineapple pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Add ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: school rolls (plain)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until flour is light.
Put next 3 ingredients in a bowl and let dissolve.
Add shortening to yeast mixture.
Add liquid mixture to flour and beat well.
You may have to add a little more flour a little at a time.
(Let rise until double.)
Punch down.
Pinch out rolls and place in a greased pan. Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: marinade for grilled chicken
directions: Mix Western dressing, apricot preserves and onion soup mix; pour over chicken.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours.
Grill chicken. Brush on sauce during grilling.

title: orange cookies with nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream first 4 ingredients; beat well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Mix gently until just blended; add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased heavy-duty foil; bake until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Bake 3 layers at 325° for 25 minutes. Let cool thoroughly and frost.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Mix remainder of ingredients and simmer.

title: seasoned flour for chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Coat chicken.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crispy oven "fried" chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a broiler pan with cooking spray. In paper or plastic bag, combine cereal and spices.
Place egg white in shallow bowl; beat slightly.
Dip chicken pieces in egg white.
Shake dipped chicken in cereal mixture to coat.
Place on sprayed broiler pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until fork-tender and juices run clear.
Serves 6.
(Low-fat recipe.)

title: low-fat banana milkshake
directions: Blend in blender; process until smooth.
Serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Combine next seven ingredients.
Heat a large iron skillet and pour half of the batter into it.
Layer beef, cheese, onion and peppers over batter.
Pour the remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn tamale treat
directions: Saute onion
in
margarine.
Add
tamales, mixing well. Stir in	corn;
add salt.
Spoon into 1-quart (greased) casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Scoop potato "meat" out of shells while still hot.
Mix all ingredients well and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sicilian rigatoni and sausage
directions: In medium skillet, cook sausage, green pepper and onion until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in pasta sauce, sugar and fennel.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Prepare rigatoni according to package directions; drain. Add olive oil and toss to coat.
Serve with sauce.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham and egg souffl
directions: Trim the crusts from the bread. Butter the bread on both sides and lay as a crust in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Sprinkle over bread the cubed ham. Toss grated cheese over all. Beat eggs and milk. Pour over the mixture. Bake* at 325° for 45 minutes until golden brown. Serve at once.

title: girl scout thin mint cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, 3 tablespoons of shortening (melted), cake flour, and egg in a large bowl.
Add the water a little bit at a time until the dough forms.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
tags: Betty Crocker chocolate fudge cake mix

title: shrimp boats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add 1 cup onion, bell pepper, cayenne and garlic; saute over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and saute about 4 more minutes until pink.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.
Cut French bread in half lengthwise; scoop out soft center.
Toast bread that was scooped out and crumble into shrimp mixture.
Divide shrimp mixture and spoon into shells.
Layer Cheddar and Mozzarella over shrimp.
Top with olives and remaining 1 cup onion.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, pineapple and coconut.
Melt margarine and add.
Put in uncooked pie shells and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yum yums
directions: Beat
1 egg; melt margarine and mix with cake mix.
Mix with spoon
until stiff. Grease and flour 8 1/4 x 13-inch pan. Press mixture into pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Pour
on
top
of
first
layer.
Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Stew chicken in water until done (or microwave).
Drain chicken, reserving broth.
Combine mushroom soup, broth, chilies, and sour cream.
Saute onion and garlic and add to sauce.
Add seasonings and chicken to sauce.
Grate and mix cheeses.
Soften tortillas in oil and then cut into strips.
Layer in dish, tortillas, then sauce, then cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese layer.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Tortillas may also be filled in traditional rolled style.

title: "branana" muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and spices. Set aside.
Stir together cereal, milk and bananas in mixing bowl. Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add egg whites and Promise spread to cereal mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture; stir in raisins, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
12 muffins.
Per serving: 1 muffin, 150 calories, 2 g dietary fiber, 4 g fat.

title: tuna chip casserole
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper and brown slightly.
Add milk; cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add tuna and remove from flame.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and cover bottom with 1/4 the potato chips which have been crushed.
Top with 1/2 the creamed tuna. Repeat.
Cover with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: curried beef
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 12 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: barbecued pork and basting sauce
directions: Combine all spices.
Rub into roast.
Let it stand several hours or place in plastic bag and refrigerate overnight.
Warm to room temperature before putting on spit.
Insert a meat thermometer and brown on spit for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs.
Stir in milk, blueberries, oil, water and juice concentrate.
Combine dry ingredients separately.
Stir into liquid mixture until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put in crock-pot on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: hoka chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Slice one roll of dough and line bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix cream cheese, sour cream, eggs, and sugar. Spread on first layer. Slice other roll of dough and place on top. Bake one hour at 300°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix butter, Eagle Brand, salt, confectioners sugar and pecans. Roll into small balls and let dry.
After candy balls have dried, place chocolate, paraffin wax, vanilla and black walnut flavoring in top of a double boiler.
Melt.
Dip candy balls into hot chocolate mix with a toothpick.
Place on waxed paper.
Allow to dry.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cook chicken wings (frozen
or	thawed)
in hot cooking oil until brown or golden.
Dip
in
hot
sauce,
coating both sides. Place in shallow
baking
pan/sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until
done.
Serve with celery stalks and Blue cheese dressing.
This
is
a
big favorite dish anytime, anywhere.

title: morning shake
directions: In the container of an electric blender, place milk, banana, orange juice and vanilla.
Cover and whirl until smooth.
Serve at once.
Yield:
2 portions (about 2 cups).

title: fudgy walnut pudding
directions: Pour into ungreased pan.
Top with chocolate cake batter. Bake 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend all together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill for at least 1 hour (longer is better).
Pies may be frozen.

title: in and out coffee cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Mix on low speed until blended. Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl for topping. Add 1/2 topping to batter and mix slightly. Spread batter in greased 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with remainder of topping. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt oleo in iron skillet; add other ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: ann's banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and mix together with eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to banana mixture.
Add nuts and melted butter or margarine and flavoring.
Pour into buttered loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Amount prepared will depend on number of persons to be served. Can be served with soft tortillas or tortilla chips.
Place on serving table in order listed.
Take small servings and layer on plate...by the time you get all of this on your plate, it is full.

title: cheese caraway batter bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cheese, shortening, sugar, salt, caraway seed and 2 cups of flour. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl. Cover; let rise in a warm place until double, about 30 minutes.

title: plantation bars(the magic of the microwave)
directions: Microwave (High) coating in uncovered 3-quart microwavable casserole 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add peanuts and cereal; mix to coat evenly.
Grease 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Spoon mixture into pan; press evenly.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes about 60 bars.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil to 260° (hard ball stage); takes about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda, quickly, then pour over popcorn in a large roasting pan.
Stir gently until all kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Turn out onto waxed paper; spread apart and allow to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: salmon steaks teriyaki
directions: Place salmon steaks in shallow pan.
Combine oil, lemon juice, soy, dry mustard, ginger and garlic powder; pour over steaks.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour, turning once.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place steaks on broiler pan.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 5 minutes; turn and brush again.
Broil 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line square buttered pan with bread.
Trim to fit.
Place sliced meat over bread.
Mix eggs, soup and milk with fork.
Pour over bread and meat.
Top with cheese of your choice, fairly thick.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells almost complete amount of time, but don't overcook (add a little oil to the water so they don't stick).

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger meat, cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into a baking dish. Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add soup; blend until smooth. Remove from heat and add sour cream, salt, pepper, onions and 1 cup cheese.
Put potatoes and sauce in baking dish.
Sprinkle other cup of cheese on top.
You can also sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made day before use.
Tastes like baked potato with all the trimmings.

title: corn and ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until top is browned and center is done.

title: lazy jake
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch iron skillet or baker and heat in preheated 450° oven.
Mix ingredients and pour into heated pan. Mixture should be the consistency of a "batter." Bake until light golden brown.
Turn out immediately onto plate or platter.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice and boil peeled eggplant in salted water until tender. Drain the water off.
Mash and add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and milk.
Add 1/2 cup cheese on top of casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When nearly done, add sweet milk.
Pour over top.

title: orange butter
directions: Beat butter or margarine and peel until fluffy.

title: old-fashioned vinegar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, and cook until thick. Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and add 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Top the pie and bake about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Allow egg whites to warm up to room temperature.
Use 2 pieces of wax paper; sift flour and 1/2 cup of sugar together 4 times.
Beat egg whites and salt with hand beater until foamy.
Sprinkle in cream of tartar and continue beating until whites are stiff enough to stand in soft peaks, but still moist and glossy.
Then add 1 cup of sugar in 4 additions (1/4 cup at a time) over whites and beating 25 strokes.
Add flavorings and beat 10 strokes.
Then sift in flour mixture 1/4 at a time.
Fold in the flour lightly with a wooden spoon, using 15 complete foldover strokes for each addition.
Use 10 extra strokes for last addition.
Pour batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 30 to 35 minutes.

When done, remove from oven, invert on wire rack and let stand 1 hour or until cold. When cold, tilt cake pan on its side; carefully loosen cake from sides of pan and around center tube using a knife.
Then invert cake on a cake rack and lift off pan.
If cake doesn't turn out easily, loosen it again, then turn cake right side up.
Dust with powdered sugar and serve with Fresh Peach Ice Cream.

title: chipper dipper(chicken fajita)
directions: Fajitas can be very simple to make and this one is perfect for breakfast or lunch.

title: white fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and cream cheese.
Add nuts and stir until golden brown.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Spread in pan or dish.

title: italian salad
directions: This is a good basic salad that children love.
Be sure to cut everything up very small.
Place the Romaine in your bowl, then the watercress, chopped vegetables.
Strew the sprouts and garbanzo beans on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients together, except cornflakes and melted butter.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with mixture of cornflakes and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream cake (2)
directions: With mixer, mix ice cream, pudding and milk.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Mix crackers, margarine and nuts well.
Pat 2/3 mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not bake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing and toss with salad ingredients.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles; set aside; drain.
Roll Pepperidge Farm dressing with dough roller to make them fine.
Put in layers in greased pan 1 cup dressing, cream of chicken soup, noodles, peas and carrots, and chicken broth.	Sprinkle with remaining dressing on top.
Cover with foil.	Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans and walnuts
directions: Cook beans in a large pot of boiling water until just tender, about five minutes.
Rinse beans with cold water to stop the cooking.
Beans may be cooked in advance, about 6 hours before you serve them.
Be sure to refrigerate them.
To complete, put butter with oil in large heavy skillet over high heat.
Add beans and toss until heated through, about 4 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add walnuts and parsley and toss.

title: caramel rice krispies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Stir in cereal and pat into 9 x 13 greased pan. Spread marshmallow creme over bars. Mix another batch and set aside.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine milk and soup mix until smooth.
Add uncooked macaroni, water chestnuts, chicken, onion, cheese, 3 of the eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight, remove from refrigerator.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into bowl.
Sprinkle top with nuts and coconut.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade sausage with sage
directions: Mix pork thoroughly with all ingredients.
Shape into patties the size of a biscuit.
Fry in a skillet until nicely browned on each side.

title: veal cube scallopini
directions: Roll veal cubes in seasoned flour and fry in hot oil until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir together.
Cover and cook on low heat or in slow cooker for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or fettucine noodles.

title: easy white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil rapidly, without stirring, until small amount forms soft ball in cold water.
Pour syrup in fine stream over egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla. Continue beating 10 to 15 minutes or until frosting is right consistency to spread.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease a shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Mix	undiluted
soup
and
milk
in a large bowl until blended.
Add
remaining ingredients, except cheese and toss gently to mix.
Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over
top.	Bake
minutes
or until hot and bubbly. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Peel and boil potatoes until tender, drain well.
Use an electric mixer to mix potatoes, 1 stick of butter, white sugar and evaporated milk.
Beat until smooth (if mixture is too stiff, add more evaporated milk).
Beat in eggs and add cinnamon.
Pour into large buttered casserole dish.

title: baked virginia apples
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Remove core from each section and cut each quarter into 3 wedges.
Arrange slices in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and spices and sprinkle over apples.
Pour 1 cup water over all and dot generously with butter.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: easter bunny smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and whirl until smooth. Makes 2 (1 cup) servings.

title: fresh vegetable gumbo
directions: Cook beef ribs, pepper, water, onion and salt on medium heat until fork-tender.
Remove meat from broth.
Add to broth tomatoes, okra and lima beans.
Cook at least 1 1/2 hours.
Add fresh corn and cook 30 minutes.
Add chicken and cook about 30 minutes.
Dice the lean meat from the ribs and add to the gumbo.
This seems like a lot of fixing, but it isn't all that much trouble and it makes a lot.
It freezes well.
Good to have on hand on "short notice" company.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl with spoon.
Make into 1 inch balls.
Press down with fork onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat until light and fluffy.

title: herb mushroom gravy
directions: In saucepan, in hot margarine, cook mushrooms with thyme until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in gravy and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Serve over chicken or mashed potatoes.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: chicken tetrazini
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar; blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mamaw's fruitcake
directions: Add soda to applesauce.
Mix dry ingredients and add to applesauce, butter and Crisco.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make 1 or 2 weeks before needed and soak with apple or orange juice to keep moist.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix celery, bell pepper, onion, Mrs. Dash, hot sauce, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add crabmeat.
Imitation crabmeat is good with this recipe.

title: chocolate refrigerator pie
directions: Grease well one 10-inch pie pan.
Beat egg whites with sugar and vinegar.
Bake 30 minutes at 275°.
Increase heat to 300° for 15 minutes.
Let cool in oven with door open.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells while stirring to keep pecans from settling to the bottom while pouring. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions on package or you can make your own pudding using skim milk. Cool. Before serving, fold in the drained mandarin oranges and the sherry.

title: quick and easy polynesian rice
directions: Prepare the package of rice as directed.
Stir in the meat, pineapple, peas and garlic.
Heat thoroughly all ingredients.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, pudding, fruit cocktail, and nuts. Form into a large ball.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours or more. Serve on cinnamon graham crackers.

title: ice cube punch
directions: Soak plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve 1 cup hot water and then add sugar.
Have ready, pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Pour into gelatin mixture.
Put into ice cube trays and freeze.
When ready to serve, fill glass with cubes and fill with ginger ale.

title: pudding cake
directions: Melt butter and combine with flour and pecans.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; pour over cooled crust.
Mix the puddings and milk; pour over the cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: northern beans
directions: Chop onion, pepper, garlic and sausage.
Saute in olive oil and add oregano.
Add beans and cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: super easy chicken tortilla soup
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in olive oil until soft. You may add other vegetables if you would like. Remove chicken from the bone and shred. Add salsa to vegetables. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: fat-free cocoa
directions: Boil cocoa, water and sugar 3 minutes.
Add milk, additional water, salt and cinnamon.
Heat, but do not let boil.
Add vanilla just before serving.
Serves approximately 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla, powdered sugar, Rice Krispies together.
Make 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening over medium heat.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Set until cool.
They will harden when cool.

title: no bake bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheerios, rice cereal, peanuts, and M&M's and set aside. In a saucepan, bring syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring often. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over cereal mixture and toss to coat evenly. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a frying pan.
Chop onion and put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: hot roll filled bread
directions: Mix dough according to directions.
Let rise.
Roll out lengthwise.
Spread lightly with margarine and cover with meats and cheese.
Let beaten egg drizzle over 1-inch from edges.
Roll up lengthwise.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in bowl and set aside.
Combine brown sugar, white sugar, butter and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add eggs and dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups of chocolate chips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 or 10 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put melted butter in pan (13 x 9-inch). Mix well the sugar, salt, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this mixture over melted butter.
Add can of fruit over top of mixture, but do not stir.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add parsley, sage, salt and pepper.
Put bread in large bowl.
Mix eggs and water.
Pour margarine mixture over bread, then add egg-water mixture.
Mix thoroughly.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except shredded Cheddar cheese). Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: crock-pot sweet and sour pork
directions: Place in crock-pot.
Cook at low all day.

title: cinnamon roll
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat to soft-ball stage, stirring constantly.
Take off heat; whip until it loses its gloss and starts to harden.
Add vanilla and beat in well.
Add pecan halves until candy is used up. Tear off waxed paper, about 2 feet long.
Sprinkle cinnamon about 4-inches wide down center of waxed paper.
Drop candy on paper, forming into a log.
Let harden.
Slice and eat.
Can be frozen and served later.
Be sure to wrap in foil to freeze or keep out.

title: nests
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients and shape into balls.
Dip into egg whites and roll in nuts.
Bake for 5 minutes in a 300° oven.
Remove from oven and make a thumbprint and fill with jam or jelly. Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and pecans together.
After these ingredients have been mixed well, make into small round balls.
Let set overnight.
Melt chocolate chips or if you prefer, 1/2 pound Baker's chocolate (semi-sweet) and paraffin wax in top of double boiler and melt.
After it's melted, put ball on toothpick and dip into chocolate mixture.
Yields 90 pieces of candy.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat thoroughly and pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: simple peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Lay drained peaches on margarine. Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl and pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Line pie pan with pie crust.
Prick crust with fork, then brown at 350°.
In saucepan mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg mixture. Slowly pour egg mixture into saucepan, stirring rapidly.
Cook 2 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Brown 1/3 cup coconut.
Put whipped topping on pie and sprinkle with coconut.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs
until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla,
mixing until thick.
Add zucchini and stir thoroughly. Add
flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add
nuts and stir well.
Bake in loaf pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Brown mushrooms, beef and onion in shortening.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add mushroom liquid, 57 sauce, parsley and water.
Combine well.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve immediately over noodles.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons mix per cup of water.

title: chicken casserole-mama's
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Heat and mix together soup, milk and margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Layer with onions and eggs.
Prepare stuffing mix and add to dish.
Pour 2 1/2 cups broth over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large saucepan, mix all ingredients except only 1/2 the cheese.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until everything is well blended.
Begin layering mixture, tortillas, mixture, tortillas and mixture, ending with mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Combine can milk and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into ice cream container.
Add your favorite fruit, if desired. Finish filling container with milk.
Churn until frozen.
(If using fruit, be sure to add the juice.)

title: sausage squares
directions: Spread first 3 ingredients into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Brown sausage and 1 chopped onion together.
Drain well and spread on Bisquick mixture.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage and eggs
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, then put in eggs.
Cook until golden brown.

title: homemade chip dip
directions: Dice ham into small pieces and mix with other ingredients. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Mix well.
Eat with Fritos.

title: kathy's ham salad
directions: Mix cubed cooked ham, cheese, olives, noodles, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Serve on lettuce leaf, garnish with whole olives.

title: golden lemon pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in lemon juice and extract. Add milk; beat for 30 seconds.
Sift cake flour, salt and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar for an added touch.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two 8-inch layers. Let cool. Frost with chocolate frosting. Put cherry pie filling on top of cake.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon juice and milk, then salt and melted butter.
Fold in flour and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish or individual molds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
The dish should be placed in a pan of water that is 1-inch deep. Cool.
Loosen edges of pudding; invert on serving dish with custard on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: olive pate
directions: Place ingredients in the bowl of food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Pulse several times and scrape sides of bowl down. Pulse until mixture of coarse paste.
Makes a generous cup.
Serve on toasted bread.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in skillet; remove beef.
Cook macaroni, onion and green pepper in meat fat.
Return meat along with tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to taste.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread butter on bread.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Spread this mixture on bread.
Put in oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until they boil and refrigerate overnight.
Mix slightly with mixer.
Then fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish or large bowl.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put in greased (buttered) casserole.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Stir every once in a while.

title: sweet and sour party meatballs and sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, chestnuts, onion, ginger, soy sauce, egg and bread crumbs in a large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 36 balls. Roll in flour or cornstarch to coat lightly, shaking off excess. Brown in oil in a large skillet.
Remove balls as they brown to a roasting pan; cover loosely with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.
Combine with sweet and sour sauce.

title: beef and mushroom stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, sugar, onions, vinegar, garlic and ginger.
Add beef to marinade and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Heat oil in wok.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and saute 5 minutes.
Add beef and marinade.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Chop vegetables, then saute until tender. In large bowl, whip eggs and milk. Add spinach, cheese and sauteed vegetables to milk/egg mixture. Pour mixture into pie shells. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when stuck into the middle of the quiche.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Brown bacon in frying pan; drain and set aside.
Saute onion and bell pepper in same pan.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot on high until well heated, then simmer on low for a few hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar, flour and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in greased casserole set in pan of water.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: shrimp-celery bisque
directions: In saucepan, combine celery, potato, onion, 1 cup water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes; stir often.
Coarsely chop shrimp.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients on low speed.
Add the apple slices and nuts.
Put cake in cold oven.
Set temperature for 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on 1 yellow cake mix, 2 sticks melted butter and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: peanut delite dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and peanuts.
Press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cream together the peanut butter and cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over first layer.
Mix milk, chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding.
Spread over second layer. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream together and form into two balls.
Coat with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for storage. Set out one hour prior to serving.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine ketchup and Coke in skillet.
Add chicken.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Uncover and simmer for about 30 more minutes, basting occasionally. Sauce will thicken.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Slice half the cake in thin slices and cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save the rest of the cake for the second layer. Mix the rest of the ingredients, except the pie filling.
Spread half the mixture over cake in pan.
Use remaining cake for second layer.
Spread with remainder of mixture.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine and broth.
Put dressing in broth.
Mix soup and heat until thick.
Put 1/2 of dressing in bottom of dish, then turkey, then soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Wash in warm water and drain. Mix with all remaining ingredients.

title: irish potato candy
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add the vanilla and sugar and beat until mixture forms a ball.
With a spoon, stir in the coconut.
Roll the mixture between your hands to form small potato shaped candies, or roll into small balls.
Place the cinnamon into a shallow dish.
Roll the balls in the cinnamon; then place on a cookie sheet; cover and chill for about one hour.

title: basic white bread
directions: Pour hot water into bowl.
Add yeast and stir.
Stir in the scalded and cooled water.
Then add the oil, salt and sugar.
Stir until well blended.

title: quick corn light bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan; set aside.
Combine cornmeal, flour and sugar in bowl.
Add buttermilk and shortening; blend thoroughly. Pour into prepared pan.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover pan with kitchen towel.
Let stand until cool. Serve warm with butter or cool with sliced ham or turkey.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except food color.
Add 1 to 2 drops of food color to dough.
Using approximately 1/4 of dough, put in cookie press. Chill remainder.
Press shapes onto cookie sheets.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes at 350° until set, but not brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread by layers, starting with chicken mixture, then layer with tortillas and then mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and onion; repeat.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nichole's breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13 baking dish with real butter. Brown sausage and drain well. Line bottom of dish with bread cubes. Crumble sausage over bread. Beat eggs; pour over sausage. Sprinkle with cheese. Pour milk over entire casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. May be prepared the night before. Serve with grits.

title: ham casserole
directions: Layer noodles and ham in casserole; mix remaining ingredients. Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: snow on the mountain raisin pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups coconut and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pat onto bottom and sides on a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, Knox gelatine, salt, coffee and 2 egg yolks.
Stir in 1 cup milk and mix until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar and gelatine dissolve.
Do not boil.
Add nuts and raisins.
Chill until just starts to thicken.
Beat 2 egg whites on high until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until forms stiff peaks.
Fold into gelatin mixture until no white streaks remain.
Beat 1/2 cup cream and fold into mixture.
Pour in pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut.
Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together pudding and milk until thick; set aside.
In another bowl, cream together oleo, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix this together with pudding mixture and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crushed cookies with cream mixture in large bowl, beginning and ending with crushed cookies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, with the exception of 1/2 cup parsley and 1/2 cup pecans.
Form into balls and roll in remaining pecans and parsley.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Slice raw potatoes on a sheet of aluminum foil (about 2 inch depth).
Cover with a layer of sliced sweet onions, shredded sharp cheese and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley flakes to taste.
Cover with another sheet of foil and seal edges tight.
Either bake in a moderate 350° oven or can be cooked on outdoor barbecue grill until potatoes are done.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix together sweetened condensed milk, evaporated milk and sugar.
Add peach soda, jello and peaches.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Rinse rice.
Add rice to broth; bring to boil, then simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
Drain through paper towel.
Transfer rice to serving bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: old time gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs; beat in sugar, molasses and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately to egg mixture with the milk.
Pour into large black skillet and bake at 300° until done or pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased and floured and bake approximately 45 minutes or until tests done.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in half of the margarine until onion is translucent.
Add rice and stir over low heat until rice is coated.
Stir in broth.
Add parsley, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover and bake in preheated 400° oven for 17 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Discard herbs and stir in remaining margarine.

title: stove top cherry cobbler
directions: Heat pie filling and orange juice in an 8-inch skillet, stirring occasionally.
Stir baking mix, orange peel, sugar and milk to soft dough.
Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls onto boiling cherry mixture.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes; cover and cook 10 more minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and peanut butter over medium heat until mixture boils. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add oats, marshmallows and vanilla. Stir mixture until well blended and slightly thickened. Drop from teaspoon on wax paper. Let cool. Makes approximately 48.

title: crispy parsnips
directions: Cook parsnips in boiling water; drain.
Cool.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Roll in melted margarine.
Set on plate to chill.
Dredge with flour.
Saute in margarine until crisp.

title: lois' ripe tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes; chop all vegetables.
Mix and sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Squeeze liquid out of veggies and add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boil (don't cook) and seal.

title: frozen eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar together until light and creamy.
Add milk and liquors to mixture.
Fold in egg whites that have been beaten stiff with 1/4 cup sugar.
Lastly, fold in whipped cream.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water 7 to 9 minutes or just until crisp-tender; drain. In a large saucepan, cook onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender, but not brown. Stir in flour, salt, mustard, celery salt and pepper. Add the milk all at once. Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in Velveeta until melted. Add carrots and stir to coat. Transfer to a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Toss bread cubes and 1/3 cup melted butter to coat; sprinkle over carrots. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and cubes are lightly toasted. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare two (8-inch) round cake pans; first grease and then flour the bottom and sides of the cake pans. Into large bowl, measure all ingredients, except frosting, banana slices and lemon juice.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl; then beat at high speed 5 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pour batter into pans and bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted deep into center of cake comes out clean.
Cool layers in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes; then remove from pans and cool completely on racks before filling and frosting cake.

title: apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/4 cup red hots and 1 cup of liquids, including the pineapple juice.
Add sugar.
Let mixture set until it starts to jell.
Add apples, celery and drained pineapple.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.

title: homemade bubble bath
directions: Store in tightly covered bottle or jar.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons to running water.

title: alice copeland's pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add lemon juice and extract.
Blend in flour and whipping cream alternately, beginning and ending with flour and beating well after each.
Put in cold oven set at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes (approximately).

title: no eggs no bake cheese torte
directions: Crush graham crackers and add sugar and melted oleo.
Pat in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some to sprinkle on top of cake.

title: rice pudding
directions: Sprinkle nutmeg over top of pudding; set baking dish in a shallow pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Custard will set more while cooking.

title: tuna biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flatten biscuits and lay in muffin tins.
Spoon chicken or tuna salad in the middle of biscuits. Bake until biscuits are light brown.
Crisscross top with cheese strips and let melt.

title: champagned fruit
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Place fruits in pretty bowl and pour hot syrup over all.
Pour champagne over fruit.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix all
except chocolate chips together and press into a 13 x 9
x 2-inch pan.
Melt large bag of chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate
for	30 minutes.
Remove and cut into squares.
Store in airtight container and keep cool.

title: vidalia onion and steak salad
directions: Combine parsley, oil, water, vinegar and garlic; mix well. Combine remaining ingredients, except Blue cheese and lettuce. Pour oil mixture over other ingredients; toss well.
Line large bowl with lettuce leaves; spoon salad over leaves.
Sprinkle with Blue cheese.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook one minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place chicken in heavy large saucepan. Add cold water, cover and bring to simmer.
Cook until tender (15 minutes).
Drain, remove skin and cut into cubes.
Drain beans. Heat oil in same pot over medium-high heat.
Add onions and saute until translucent, about 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano, cloves and cayenne; saute for 10 minutes.
Add beans and stock; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours.
Add chicken and 1 cup of cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with remaining cheese, sour cream, salsa and cilantro.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until thickened.
Pour into pie crust.
Cool and add whipped cream.
Top with pecans.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa; gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick.
Take off burner and add vanilla.
Serve.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Blend hot coffee and cocoa together; set aside to cool.
Sift flour, 1 1/3 cups sugar, soda and salt into bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add in order:
oil, egg yolks, vanilla and cooked coffee mixture.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large bowl until foamy.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar. Continue until meringue forms stiff glossy peaks.
Pour chocolate mixture gradually over meringue; fold in.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Increase oven temperature to 350° after cake has baked for 55 minutes, then bake 15 minutes longer.
Insert pan and let stand until cold.
Frost with Heavenly Frosting.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except onion, meat and cheese. Saute onion and meat together.
Pour half of the cornmeal mixture into a greased, large, deep black skillet (10 1/2-inch). Alternate layers of meat and cheese.
Top with remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Remove hash browns from freezer for 1/2 hour to defrost.
Mix ingredients and add salt and pepper.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan greased with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate candy
directions: Melt chips in microwave until smooth (stir after every 30 to 40 seconds).
Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls into paper candy cups. Cool completely.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, omitting salt; drain.
Place broccoli in baking dish.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and egg in bowl; mix well.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle mixture of crumbs and butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snack crackers
directions: In saucepan, melt brown sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with Eagle Brand milk.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in marshmallows last and mix. Butter Bundt pan well and pack very hard.
Refrigerate in Bundt pan about 3 days.
Stir in warm water to loosen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease pan with Pam or oleo.
Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and sprinkle onion soup mix on rice.
Add water and place chicken in single layer on rice.
Spoon chicken soup on all parts of chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: no name cake
directions: Blend together the first 6 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes, then add mini bits and nuts.
Stir until blended. Bake in Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and corn. Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut brittle(easy)
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and margarine in electric frypan at 375°.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until syrup turns golden brown.
Stir in peanuts that have been warmed in oven.
Continue stirring until golden brown.
Add soda; stir vigorously.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and cut to size.

title: 9-inch graham cracker crust
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
mixing
well.
Firmly press mixture evenly over bottom and sides of pie plate.
For frozen pies, crust needs no baking.
For other pies, bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Yield: 1 crust.

title: western burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well and season with salt, garlic salt, season salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Make a recipe for "Hot Rolls" and let rise.
Knead and roll flat.
Make a 6-inch circle.
Put mustard, shredded cheese and 1 heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture on the circle.
Fold dough over to enclose ingredients in dough.
Put closed side down in oil.
Put a dab of oil on top of roll.
Let rise.
Cook at 400° until done.

title: marinated vegetable and rice salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine all vegetables and cooked rice in a large container.
Heat water, oil, vinegar, sugar and salt almost to boiling. Allow to cool slightly; pour over vegetables and rice.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serves 12 to 15.

title: recess cups
directions: Cut cupcake liners and put in cupcake pan.
Melt Hershey bar; add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Over hot water, melt 1 cup peanut butter in Pyrex measuring cup.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 4 egg whites stiff; gradually add sugar. Spread over cracker crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
When cool, add 2 cans lemon pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into balls.
Brown meat balls in shortening until cooked through. Mix cornstarch and sugar; stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir until smooth.
Heat and thicken in pan, then pour over meat balls.
Add tidbits and green pepper; heat through.

title: sausage and rice casserole for microwave
directions: Brown sausage on full power for 4 minutes; drain well. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Microwave on full power or High for 14 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: avocado-salsa dip
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (if using a glass dish, heat to 325°). Saute vegetables in butter until soft.
Beat eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
After cooling vegetables, add them to milk mixture. Fold in cheese.
Crumble sausage in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked ham with beer
directions: Ask butcher to score ham in diamond shapes.
Preheat oven (350°).
Place ham in a deep roasting pan and add beer.
Cover pan and bake for about 20 minutes.
(Actually the ham is virtually in the oven heat.)
Baste the ham 2 or 3 times during this cooking period.
Remove ham from pan and cool for about 20 minutes.

title: nutty spaghetti
directions: Mix walnuts, black olives, pimento, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix garlic into olive oil and toss with walnut mixture. Serve over cooked, drained spaghetti.

title: magnificent nachos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Spread beans in a greased 9-inch round dish. Spoon meat on beans.
Top meat with chilies, then sprinkle with cheese.
Pour taco sauce over all; cover with waxed paper.
Warm in microwave.
Serve with chips of your choice.

title: potato easy
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle potato chips or bread crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until very brown and crisp around the edges.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Crust:
Mix vanilla wafers, salted peanuts and butter together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Brown 1 pound hamburger and 1 small chopped onion.
Drain. Add 3 cups tomatoes, 1 teaspoon chili powder, 1/2 cup uncooked rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until rice is tender.
Add 1 medium zucchini, chopped and 1/4 pound Velveeta cheese cut up. Pour into greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tex-mex steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces and pound to tenderize.
Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown steak.
Add more oil if needed to brown all of the steak.
Cover and cook on low while preparing salsa mixture.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Use a 1 gallon glass container.
Boil celery seed, salt, vinegar and sugar; let cool.
Add onions, pepper, pimentos and garlic.
As cucumbers are ready, slice and put in jar; stir twice daily.
No need to change or add to solution.
You can start eating after 3 days.
Will keep for months.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split muffins in half by piercing them around edges with the tines of a fork and prying them apart gently.
Place split sides up in shallow baking dish.
Spoon tomato sauce onto muffins, spreading it to the edges.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is browned slightly at the edges.
Makes 4.

title: punch
directions: Mix all liquids; chill.
Add pineapple sherbet when ready to serve.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour.
Beat in melted butter, eggs, milk and white syrup.
Add the vanilla.
Beat the mixture with a wooden spoon.
Place pecans in the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes (until set in the middle).
Will make a 10-inch pie.
(For an 8-inch pie, use only 2 eggs.)

title: heavenly fish fillet
directions: Mix lemon juice and wine and pour over fish.
Let stand for one hour or more.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onion and hot sauce. Place marinated fish on foil in broiler pan and broil 5 to 7 minutes or until flaky.
Remove from broiler and spread mix over fish.
Rebroil 2 to 3 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Drain clams well.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; heat on medium-high for 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust 10 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.
Mix first 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add strawberry jello and mix thoroughly. Place berries in pie crust with stem end down.
Pour mixture over berries.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cooked chicken or turkey salad
directions: Use wok or large skillet.
Cook the chicken in peanut oil. Add celery and carrots.
Cook until tender, then add tomatoes, onion and wine.
Cook for about 2 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Can be served on lettuce or bread.

title: harvest bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Heat cottage cheese in small saucepan over low heat until warm, but not hot; remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, yeast, sugar, salt, soda, eggs and 1 cup of flour in large bowl; beat at medium speed of electric mixer 2 minutes.
Gradually mix in remaining flour to form soft dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Cover and let rise in a warm place free from drafts until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn dough out onto a floured board; divide dough into 24 equal pieces and shape each into a ball.
Place balls in 2 greased 9-inch round baking pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven and brush with melted butter.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: sundae brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously prick bottom and sides of pie shell with a fork and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: jo's baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar, ketchup, onion and spices.
Put in greased pot or casserole.
Sprinkle bacon on top and cover with corn flakes, crunched.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks; drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: lite banana-raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except cereal and set aside.
In a 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl add cereal, milk and water allowing cereal to moisten.
Then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add egg and mashed banana, mix well.
Spray muffin tin with nonstick spray. Bake in a preheated 400° oven about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix the flour, chopped nuts and oleo.
Pat in ungreased 8 x 10-inch pan (bottom only).
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 or 35 minutes longer.

title: suet (bird feed for birds)
directions: Melt beef fat and let cool until it softens.
Reheat and let cool again.
Mix in nuts, apples, raisins, seeds and corn meal. Add enough dry ingredients to make it as thick as possible.
Place in a baking dish and freeze firm.
Cut into pieces to fit your feeder.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add gradually the sugar.
Beating constantly, add the vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt (sifted with flour).
Heat to boiling point the milk and butter.
Add all at once, beating well.
Thin batter.
Pour into an 8-inch greased pan and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and bring juice to a boil.
Add jello.
Cool until syrupy.
Mix pineapple and cream cheese together and then add the rest of the ingredients, except jello.
After mixing, add all to jello.

title: festive fudge-filled bars
directions: Mix oats, flour, nuts, sugar, soda and salt.
Cream in the butter.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups and press remaining mixture into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Melt shortening and M&M's together (save out 1 cup M&M's).
Remove this from heat and add milk; mix well.
Spread chocolate mixture over baked crust.
Do not spread to edges.
Combine reserved crumb mixture, coconut and M&M's.
Pour this mixture over chocolate in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.

title: cheese rolls(freeze well)
directions: Have cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well, using fingers if necessary.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch diameter rolls.
Wrap in wax paper, seal and freeze. While still cold, slice thinly.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix well until all blended.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken divine
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread broccoli on bottom of pan, then chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream, lemon juice and cheese together.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pastry crust(healthful eating)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
Pour olive oil and milk into a small bowl (do not stir); add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir lightly with a fork or pastry blender.
Using hands, form dough into two balls.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: hash brown potatoes casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together all but last two ingredients.
Place on potatoes.
Top with cornflakes and melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream together butter, water, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour and pecans.
Stir well.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 325° until brown (8 to 10 minutes).
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: carrot salad with lemon
directions: In small bowl whisk together lemon juice and salt.
Whisk in oils until well blended.
In medium size bowl combine carrots and garlic.
Pour in dressing from small bowl and toss to coat well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: blushing pear salad
directions: Soak pear halves in own liquid with several drops of food coloring in refrigerator until pears reach a desired pink (blush) color.
Drain pears thoroughly.
Place lettuce leaves onto plate. Arrange pears on top of lettuce with core side up.
Drop a tablespoon mayonnaise into pears indentation.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix ingredients together well and chill.

title: overnight chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and salt.
Cover with water.
Cook until done. Remove skin and bones.
Coarsely chop and set aside.
Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in baking dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Spoon half over broccoli.
Arrange chicken over sauce.
Top chicken with remaining sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Toss chicken and egg until coated.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cornstarch over chicken; toss.
Melt shortening in medium skillet. Add chicken; heat until brown.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, salt and water in a large bowl.
Put yeast in and set in warm place for 5 minutes.
Mix in flour.
Let rise until doubled.
Make into loaves or buns.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon party ball(a beautiful and popular addition to a buffet table)
directions: Thoroughly mix together.
Roll into ball; wrap in wax paper and chill several hours.
Then combine 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons chopped parsley and roll the party ball in this mixture.

title: crock-pot bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in water and soak overnight.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Place soaked beans in a 2-quart crock-pot.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover with water. Cook on high at least 8 hours.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans and chill.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and egg, mixing well. Insert skewer lengthwise into each wiener.
Dip or roll the skewered wieners, one at a time, in the batter and fry in deep hot fat (400°) until golden brown.
(Note:
If grease is not hot enough, batter will slide off the wieners.)

title: dixie's cucumbers
directions: Mix together and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Don't drain.
Store in refrigerator up to three months.
Can add green pepper (diced), if desired.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature and mix together adding cheese.
Blend with hands to mix thoroughly.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 400° until beginning to brown.
Recipe freezes well.

title: chewy squares
directions: Combine and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: 24 hour coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours before using. Do not try to use before the 24 hours are up.

title: vanilla bean cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with tines of fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Grind vanilla bean to consistency of pepper and mix with confectioners sugar.
While still hot, roll cookies in vanilla bean mixture.

title: peanut butter fluff
directions: Mix peanut butter, light corn syrup, sugar and salt together. Stir in heavy cream.
Whip with rotary beaters until mixture forms soft peaks, when beaters are raised.
Use as frosting, topping or filling for cake or refrigerator dessert.
Makes 2 cups.

title: swiss steak(microwave)
directions: Rub meat with garlic.
Pound flour into meat.
Place remaining ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, or cook level 3 for 2 3/4 to 3 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn meat over halfway through cooking time.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix egg, butter and cake mix; this will be very stiff so you will need to pat into pan.
Beat eggs and cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth; pour on top of first mixture in pan. Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pork chops l'orange
directions: Brown pork chops in large frying pan.
Set aside.
Then brown onions.
Add orange juice, ginger and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Carefully simmer for 15 minutes or so.
Meanwhile, make Minute rice.
Then just serve your pork chops and pour the orange sauce over the rice.
This is a quick, easy and very delicious meal everyone will enjoy, including the kids.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil noodles and drain. Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix egg with Ricotta cheese.
Add Mozzarella cheese.

title: peach honey
directions: Peel and slice ripe peaches, removing bad spots.
Put in large, heavy pan with sugar and cook over medium heat until it reaches a good boil, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice. Continue cooking until thick; stir constantly.
Put in sterilized jars and seals.

title: fried eggs(easy camp dessert)
directions: Spoon cream on plate.
Place drained peach halves (hollow side down) on cream.
Sprinkle with coconut, nutmeg or ginger.

title: sour cream capers sauce
directions: Place egg yolks in the top of a double boiler.
Stir in sour cream, vinegar and seasonings.
Cook on low heat, continue stirring until smooth and thickened.
Serve with seafood.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brandy butter
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together in a bowl until pale and fluffy.
Beat in the brandy.
Chill if not serving immediately. This may be made up to 2 days in advance and kept covered and chilled.
Serve at room temperature.
Yield:
About 3/4 cup.

title: white bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add flour and beat well.
Place in large greased bowl and cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Place back in bowl and let rise again, about 1/2 hour.
Punch down and shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Combine with other mixture.
Shape into balls and dip in white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Press star into top and return to bake 2 to 3 minutes or until light brown.
Do not let get too dark.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: instant brazilian black beans and rice for two
directions: Chop onion and garlic; saute.
Mix in black beans.
Cook on low for 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, cook rice.
Serve beans over rice.
Nice side dish.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350° in slightly greased and floured 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and berries in heavy saucepan over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally, and boil exactly 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add powdered jello as it comes from the package.
Stir to blend. Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add strawberries and dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Add nuts.
Mix well after each addition.
Bake in 2 or 3 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Slices may be topped with Philadelphia strawberry cream cheese.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat broiler.
In small pan over low heat, melt margarine. Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook about 3 minutes until garlic is tender.
Stir in wine and parsley; cook about 2 minutes longer. Arrange shrimp on foil-lined broiler pan.
Pour margarine mixture evenly over shrimp.
Broil 3-inches from heat source, about 5 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and pat into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream together next 3 ingredients. Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Mix jello with boiling water. When jello is dissolved, add strawberries or raspberries and stir. When almost set, spread over cream mixture.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix soup and water and pour over the chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine and pour over the chicken and sliced eggs.
Pour the broth over the chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until crust rises to the top and is golden brown.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast 1/2 cup coconut; set aside.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; cool slightly.
In medium bowl, beat eggs; add sweetened condensed milk, water, vanilla, salt and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared shell.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lulu paste
directions: Grind everything together (processor).
Add a dash of salt and a dash of red pepper.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup catsup and 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon chili sauce.
Put into blender until well blended.

title: nonnie's meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend egg whites, sugar and lemon juice together.
Add food coloring until it is a "minty" green.
Add mint chocolate chips; stir well.
"Dab" on foil covered cookie sheet. Put in a 375° oven.
Shut off oven and leave for 6 hours.
Do not open oven.
Makes many, and they will keep well in airtight tins. All kids love these!

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together.
