Use as much salad dressing and sour cream as you need, just keep them equal.
Add peas last.
Chill and serve over lettuce.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box; cool.
Cream together cream cheese and milk; add instant pudding.
Set aside.
Cook crushed pineapple and cornstarch until thick; cool.
Spread cream cheese/pudding mixture over cake.
Then spread pineapple over. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: green chili stew
directions: Saute meat and onions until done. Season with salt, pepper and garlic. Add tomatoes, potatoes, chilies and about 3 cups water. Simmer on low for couple of hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place the rice in the bottom of a dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Pour soup mixture over rice.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake at 325° in covered dish for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Makes lots.

title: one pan chicken bake
directions: Lay chicken breast in baking pan. Lay 1 slice cheese on each breast. Mix soups and liquids together in large bowl, mixing well, to get as smooth as possible. Pour over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees, uncovered. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: big batch preston's chili
directions: Brown hamburger. Add green peppers, onions and tomatoes. Simmer for ten minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: tiropeta 1
directions: Heat cream of wheat in melted 1/2 cup butter until slightly browned.
Add hot milk slowly and cook until slightly thickened. Gradually add beaten eggs, stirring constantly, over slow fire for 2 minutes.
(If mixture is too thick, more milk may be added.) Remove from heat.
Mash Feta cheese with fork and add with remaining ingredients, except 1/2 pound butter and filo, to egg mixture.
Mix well.

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: Wash chicken; dust with salt and paprika.
Brown in butter. Remove and set aside.
Add flour, pepper, brown sugar and ginger to make paste in leftover butter in skillet; stir well.
Add orange juice and rind; cook until thick.
Pour over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Serve over favorite rice and spoon extra orange sauce over both.

title: "corn bake"
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl together. Grease 9 x 9 pan and bake mixture at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle 1/2 bag of shredded Cheddar cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat. Add salt, flour, curry powder and pepper.
Drain mushrooms (reserve liquid).
To liquid add water to make 1/2 cup.
Gradually add to flour mixture.
Blend in milk until smooth.
Add mushrooms.
Stir over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Arrange broccoli and chicken in a 13 x 9-inch (2-quart) pan or dish.
Pour sauce over. Put cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly (about 20 minutes). Cool slightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple with juice and sugar with cornstarch and red food coloring.
Cook all until thickened. Remove from stove.
Add raspberry gelatin.
Let cool.
Add banana slices and pecans.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) baked pie crusts.
Chill before serving.
Top with nondairy topping.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all other ingredients in order.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups hot water.
Add frozen strawberries to Jell-O and let thaw.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and gently fold into Jell-O-strawberry mixture.
Place in dessert cups or casserole dish.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake the cake in a greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Let cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except fudge frosting; mix for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread mixture on cooled cake.
Let set for a while, then frost with the fudge frosting. Microwave frosting for 30 seconds on High; stir and pour over cake.

title: apple snicker salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix as pie crust.
Reserve 1/2 cup and press rest into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie mix over crust and crumble the 1/2 cup over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until slightly brown.

title: diamond cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll as for icebox cookies.
Slice into diagonal shapes.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven until done.
Yield:
16 biscuits.

title: quick dessert
directions: In 9 x 9-inch pan, pour pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Do not mix.
Cover with nuts.
Swizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mock quiche squares
directions: Trim crust from bread; toast.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Reserve drippings and crumble bacon.
Brush toast with the bacon drippings.
Cut each slice toast into quarters.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Top each with an egg slice.
Sprinkle with few green onions.
Cut Swiss cheese slices into quarters and place one on each appetizer.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hot 'n' spicy sauce
directions: Cook sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic in a large saucepan until sausage is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, oregano, basil, black pepper and red pepper into saucepan.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more or until sauce is desired consistency, stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked and well-drained pasta.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add bananas and flour mixture alternately.
Beat well. Fold in beaten eggs and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Makes one loaf.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Peel potatoes and slice into thin slices. Spray casserole dish with cooking spray. Layer bottom of casserole with 2/3 can tuna. Cover tuna with potato slices. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer with 2/3 can tuna. Layer with 1/3 grated cheese. Pour 1/3 can evaporated milk. Add another layer of potatoes, then 2/3 can tuna, then 1/3 grated cheese, then 1/3 evaporated milk. Top with another layer of potatoes, salt and pepper to taste, and remainder of cheese. Pour remaining evaporated milk over all. Cover casserole dish and bake for about 1 hour, or until potatoes are cooked tender. Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be thin.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk.
Stir well.
Cook in greased pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Crumble and set aside.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Pour on boiling water and cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast and cold water.
Add to other mix.
Add eggs and beat.
Add salt to flour.
Stir all together in a dough.
Work into a firm lump.
Put into a greased, large mixing bowl and cover tightly.
Let rise in refrigerator.
Make rolls and let rise about an hour or time needed.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Dough will keep several days in refrigerator or may be used at once.

title: frito casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in skillet.
Add soups and bring to simmer.
Line casserole dish with corn chips.
Pour soup over and top with corn chips and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
In a separate pan, heat the last 4 ingredients together until creamy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 of Doritos, 1/2 of browned hamburger and 1/2 of grated cheese. Repeat, ending with remaining 1/3 of Doritos.
Pour sauce over top of casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into slices.
Cook until tender, drain and rinse well.
Add crackers, crumbled.
Add milk, eggs, onion, oleo, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio pecan party cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar, oil, almond extract and food coloring.
Beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add nuts.
Form balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven barbecued beef
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, brown meat in salad oil over medium heat.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Add onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Mix spices into catsup. Add tomatoes, vinegar, brown sugar and chili powder.
Mix well. Return meat to pan.
Spoon some sauce over top.
Cover and bake in 325° oven about 3 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13 inch pan. Cover the bottom of the pan with bread cubes. Brown sausage. Put sausage on top of bread. Beat eggs with 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 tsp. salt. Pour over bread and sausage. Sprinkle

2 cups of shredded cheese. This much may be refrigerated until ready to bake (overnight). Mix together 1 can of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of milk. Pour over top of casserole. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350 degrees oven or until center is set.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix together the ingredients and let the mixture stand for 15 minutes.
Pour it into a 9-inch pie shell and dot it with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add a top crust, and bake the pie at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine
meat,	rice,
seasoning and onion.
Shape into balls. Brown
in	small amount of fat in skillet.
Add tomato soup mixed with 1 can water.
Cook on slow heat until done (30 to 45 minutes).
Stir often.

title: party dogs
directions: Put jelly and Worcestershire sauce in a pan or crock-pot and stir until jelly is dissolved.
Add hot dogs and simmer for 2 hours.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box. Refrigerate until set. When set, add cream cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Fold in crushed pineapple and Cool Whip. Mix and pour in large pan. Cover with ground nuts. Put in refrigerator to set.

title: mama t's sip and slurp hot chocolate
directions: Fill cup halfway, then add hot water.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Mix egg yolks, mayonnaise, mustard and olives. Dip in egg whites.

title: fiesta cornbread
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 425° oven, 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with butter.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped pork chops(4 servings)
directions: Brown chops in hot cooking oil in heavy frypan; remove.
Add onion, soup and milk to oil in pan; blend and set aside.
Starting with potatoes, put alternate layers of potatoes and cabbage into a 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle each layer with flour.
Pour soup sauce over each layer.
Place chops on top. Cover casserole or use aluminum foil to cover pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: layered hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Saute onion.
Combine meat with onion and season with salt and pepper.
Spray covered baking dish with Pam.
Place potato slices in bottom of dish.
On top of them, add a layer of carrots and then a layer of peas.
Top it off with the browned meat and onions.
Pour the can of V-8 over the casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350° with lid on.
When done, arrange the cheese slices across the top and allow to set for 10 minutes, covered, for juices to absorb and cheese to melt.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In a pie plate, combine flour with chili powder; use to coat chicken.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Stir in remaining flour mixture, orange peel, orange juice, sugar and salt.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until chicken is tender.
Add orange sections and heat.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters well.
Remove any shell.
Add seasoning.
Beat egg.
Dip two large oysters into the egg mixture, then into crumbs. Press firmly into shape.
Place oysters on wax paper.
Store in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Dip in crumbs the second time.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on heavy brown paper. Yields 16 large oysters.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water just until tender. Drain most of water, leaving just enough to cover carrots.
Mix first 6 ingredients together in medium casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles steadily in the middle.

title: chili pecans
directions: Melt butter in measuring cup.
Add spices and mix. Put pecans in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Pour butter and spice mixture over pecans. Stir.
Cook in microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High, stirring every 2 minutes.

title: bread dough(craft)
directions: Take bread and remove crust.
Break into little pieces.
Pour glue over bread and mix well.
(May need to add more glue.)
When all absorbed and pliable, make into a ball.
Form an indentation in ball and add lemon juice and glycerin.
Mix again.
Flatten out as thin as you can.
(Add flour on top, if too sticky.)
Cut with cookie cutters.
(Dip cutters in flour to keep from sticking.)
Run nail through object to put a string through later.
Brush off nice and clean; make sure edges are smooth.
Put on flat tray; let stand for one week to dry out.
Place book on objects so they don't curl. Paint with any acrylic paint (first coat white all over).

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 375°, cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and set aside.
Cream together sugars and oil.
Add eggs, beating after each addition. Add oatmeal to the mixture.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to batter mixture.
Add vanilla. Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add Topping while cake is still warm.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch buttered and floured cake pan.
When cool, transfer to cookie sheet.
Place pudding in large bowl.
Add milk and beat slightly. Add softened cream cheese and whipped topping.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Mixture will be thick.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Spread topping evenly on cake.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Blend
mushroom
soup
and
milk.
(Keep 1/2 cup of the mixture.) Stir together all ingredients except chicken and 1/2 of the onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased 2 1/2 quart baking dish. Arrange
the
chicken
breasts on top of mixture.
Pour the remaining blend of mushroom soup and milk over the chicken and sprinkle
with
remaining onion soup mix.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.	Remove, cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sausage stuffing balls
directions: Hand mix in a bowl well.
Form balls the size of a golf ball and place into a baking pan.
Bake at 325°.
Bake until sausage is cooked.

title: strata(make ahead breakfast treat)
directions: Remove crusts from bread if desired.
Butter the front and back of bread and place a layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pound shredded cheese and 1/2 pound crumbled bacon. Repeat layer.
Mix in a bowl the eggs, milk, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over bread and refrigerate overnight. In the morning, bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted and middle is set.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Boil Karo and sugar until sugar melts. Turn off heat. Stir in peanut butter until it melts. Pour over corn flakes. Stir until coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes; add 3 to 4 cups walnut meats and boil another 2 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from scorching.
Remove from fire and stir until it gets sugary. Quickly pour on wax paper; spread evenly and then break apart with a fork.
When cool, store in airtight container.
Yummy!!!

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's beef stew
directions: Brown the chuck roast squares in iron skillet. When browned, pour in 2 cups water to release browned from bottom of pan. Pour into 4-quart pressure cooker and cook for 15 minutes. Set aside to let pressure cool down in cooker. Remove top of pressure cooker after cooled. Put in potatoes, carrots and onion soup mix. Add 2 quarts of water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and boil for 20 minutes. Top with Bisquick Dumplings.

title: avocado-topped potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth. Add avocado and milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, onion and salt.

title: ice cream treat
directions: Slice ice cream and sandwich between 2 graham crackers.
Place in Ziploc Baggies; put in freezer. Best if made ahead so cracker softens some in freezer.

title: macaroni fluff
directions: Add hot milk to bread crumbs; mix.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Fold in macaroni, grated cheese and seasonings.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Set dish in pan containing 1 inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white pizza
directions: Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine
all ingredients.
Mix with beater on low speed for 10 minutes or mix in blender.	Makes approximately 4 cups.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use one or more heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.
Real good!

title: chicken marsala
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken; cook until browned, turning once. Remove from pan.
Add shallots; cook until tender.
Add sliced mushrooms.
Add ham and chicken to skillet.
Add wine; cook, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes, or until liquid becomes slightly syrupy.
(This often takes longer than 4 minutes.)
In measuring cup or small bowl, stir broth and flour until flour dissolves; add to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serve with pasta. Makes 4 servings.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together (except for wafers, cherries and Cool Whip).
Place wafers in cupcake papers and into muffin or tart tins.
Pour batter over wafers.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool completely.
Top with cherry pie filling, or any other pie filling and Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: bible cake
directions: Good luck and have fun looking up the bible verses as you go along.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot spinach and artichoke dip
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter. Add garlic and onion. Use low-medium heat. Add cream cheese and sour cream. Add spinach and artichokes. Stir occasionally on low; add pepper, sherry, Worcestershire, lemon juice and hot sauce. Stir in cheese. Cook on low-warm for a minimum of 30 minutes until blended well. Bake in oven for awhile to brown top or just serve right away. Serve with warm baguette bread or tortilla chips. Serve Hot! It is delicious!!

title: microwave barbecued ribs
directions: Cut spareribs into individual ribs and place in bottom of a large glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven 40 to 45 minutes at "Roast" or until well done.
Turn ribs over after 20 minutes.

title: turketti casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain.
Place turkey, green pepper and onion in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Pour in mushroom soup and water; add salt, pepper, cheese and spaghetti.
With 2 forks, lightly toss until all is well mixed and coated with sauce.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; it's ready to serve or you can chill for a few hours.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar. Beat in butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lutheran casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 10 x 15-inch pan. Crush 1 double bag of potato chips and pat over the top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in 450° oven or until bubbly.
Best if assembled the day before and baked on the day to be used.
Serves 25.

title: new jersey barbecue
directions: Score meat in 4 or 5 places.
Sprinkle garlic powder and salt all over.
Add pepper.
Place in roaster with half of the water and vinegar.
Bake at 400° in oven, basting often with remaining vinegar and water, until tender.
Remove from pan and cool.
Chop or grind up.
Place in frypan and add vinegar and water mixture and pepper.
Steam over low heat until seasons through to taste.

title: microwave fudge pie
directions: Soften butter by microwaving 1 minute on 40% power or defrost setting. Add butter with remaining ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie plate. Elevate pie plate on saucer in microwave. Microwave on 60% power for 8 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares. Serve warm or topped with ice cream.

title: egg pastry pie crust
directions: Take the beaten egg and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Mix this good and add to the ingredients.
This makes 3 or 4 pie shells.

title: easy punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour Sprite and Hawaiian Punch over sherbet.
Mix well and serve.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops that have been salted, peppered and floured in oil.
When browned, pour sauce over chops.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 5 minutes, until meat is cooked.
Pour off fat.
Stir in raw vegetables; microwave 4 to 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender (still on High).
Stir in remaining ingredients and cover. Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Uncover and microwave on 50% power for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring once.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in cornbread stuffing mix. Line casserole dish with cornbread stuffing saving enough to sprinkle over top. Fill with squash mixture and place remaining crumbs on top. Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Can be reheated at same temperature for same length of time.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt, soda and baking powder, then vanilla, chopped apples and pecans.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and let cool.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground beef; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: chex party mix
directions: Mix in roasting pan and bake slow, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Turn 1/2 turn and microwave 3 more minutes.
Turn 1/2 turn and microwave 4 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread the graham cracker crumbs on top of the butter.
Layer the chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Top with the condensed milk.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: quick vidalia onion relish
directions: Mix together onions, vinegar, sugar and water.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain well and mix with mayonnaise, celery seed and pepper.

title: "moussaka" - baked eggplant or zucchini with meat
directions: There will be two layers of meat sauce and 3 layers of eggplant.
Grease lightly an 11 x 16-inch pan.
Sprinkle bottom with bread crumbs.
Alternate eggplant with meat sauce and bread crumbs and cheese and top layer will use 1/2 cup Romano cheese for sprinkling.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Divide green beans into 12 to 15 "bundles." Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each bundle. Place bundles on cookie sheet or in a baking pan. Dot each bundle with butter and sprinkle with onion salt and brown sugar. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tapioca cream pudding
directions: Reserve 2 teaspoons sugar.
Combine remaining sugar with milk, tapioca and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add egg yolk.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat (mixture will be thin).
Add vanilla.
Beat egg white to soft peaks.
Slowly add reserved 2 teaspoons sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Gradually stir into hot mixture.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour and sage.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until golden brown on both sides.
Add soup and 1/2 cup of water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soup and water in broiler pan.
Put rice in, mixing well. Lay chicken on top of rice	mixture.
Spread onion soup mix over all.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off oranges and discard.
Keep juice of pineapple and fruit cocktail.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs till light, add sugar gradually, beating till thick.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Freeze in 5-quart ice cream freezer.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the ingredients with spinach.
Mix well.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples with dry gelatin and sugar; set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk mixture and mix as pie dough.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan, lining sides and bottom.
Add apple mixture.
Cover with streusel topping. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: frozen coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in a small pan on stovetop.
Add coconut and nuts. Cook until golden brown.
In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Beat until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture.
Drizzle caramel mixture. Sprinkle melted coconut mixture and repeat.
(This recipe makes 2 pies.) Cover with foil and freeze.
Serve from freezer.

title: marie's chip bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in cracker crumbs for layer.
Next, layer the coconut, chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Pour over with condensed milk; add nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes about 24 bars.

title: orange cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Peel and run through food chopper.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to shortening along with milk and ground orange.
(Egg can be added if it is too dry). Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, ice.

title: homemade apple butter(made in crock-pot, stirring occasionally)
directions: Use large stone jar to pack kraut; sprinkle a little salt in bottom of jar, then layer of sliced or chopped cabbage, about 3 inches.
Add salt and sugar mixture, 1 tablespoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Sprinkle over cabbage.
Continue to fill jar with cabbage and the salt and sugar mixture until the jar is full. Press the cabbage down as you go.
When the jar is full, lay a dinner plate on top and weight down.
Be careful not to use too much salt.
Cover with white cloth.
Be sure to use canning salt.

title: green rice chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onions, parsley and garlic until just tender-crisp.
Remove from heat and toss in rice and chicken cubes.
Season as desired.
Pack into buttered 9 x 12-inch Pyrex casserole.
Garnish with almond slices and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.
Tossed fruit salad and rolls make this an enjoyable meal.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients; pour 1/2 of the mix in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake 6 minutes.
Melt caramels in evaporated milk; pour baked mix and sprinkle remainder of cake mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine honey, mustard, lemon, salt and pepper in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pierce chicken with knife in several places. Coat chicken with half the sauce.
Place chicken, skin side down in baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° preheated oven.
Turn chicken over and pour on the rest of sauce and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add green beans, basil, salt and broth; bring to boil.
Add rice; remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeats over lukewarm water (let stand for 10 minutes). In a separate bowl large enough to mix your bread dough, mix milk, boiling water, shortening, molasses, and salt.
Let it cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Gradually mix in the all-purpose flour, cup at a time, then beat in the whole wheat flour.
If dough becomes too thick to beat, knead it by hand.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter or oleo; add syrup and salt; beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time; add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 1 hour until filling is set or knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Peel and dice or slice.
Melt butter. Add flour, salt, Accent and pepper.
Stir to a smooth paste.
Add milk and cook until it begins to thicken.
Add parsley and pimento (optional).

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together well the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift together salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Stir into mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and eggs; add eggs and mix well. Stir in potatoes until well mixed. Garnish with paprika. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Chip meats into pieces; I use my Cuisinart.
Add Bon Appetit or Jane's Krazy Mixed-Up salt.
Combine remaining ingredients, then add meat and seasoning.

title: layered vegetable dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place layers as listed into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with tight fitting lid or foil.
Bake 2 hours.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: kolaches
directions: Moisten
yeast
cakes
in 1/2 cup warm milk and 1/2 cup sugar and
let
sit.
Add
oil,
2 cups warm milk, flour, egg yolks
and salt.
Knead
with
wooden
spoon until smooth and elastic.
Set aside and let rise to double in size.
Divide or pinch off for kolaches, pies or cinnamon rolls.

title: mango-pineapple daiquiri
directions: In blender, puree ingredients.
If you want, add 1 cup rum to mixture.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Prepare crust and roll into a rectangle to fit a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bring up on the sides to top.

title: peas 'n mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for microwave.
Put in microwave for 45 minutes on High.
Stir and let set a few minutes before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Simmer deboned chicken in melted Crisco until tender.
Drain off excess grease and add all spices and sausage.
Put in casserole dish with rice and water.
Stir well.
Cook in oven on 400° until rice is done and water is gone, approximately 45 minutes.

title: "junk" salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake until brown, 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: old fashioned egg custard(2 pies)
directions: Save 3 egg whites for meringue.
Beat eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add milk, butter, flavoring and flour; mix until smooth. Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells and cook at 300° until pies are firm.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In one bowl, cream the margarine, 1 cup sugar and eggs until light.
Add the next 5 ingredients to this bowl.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Immediately upon removal from oven, pour over top a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and juice from 1 lemon.

title: kool-aid holiday punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water in a non-metal container. Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sliced strawberries, if desired.
Makes about 7 1/2 quarts.

title: "easy" pecan pie
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart bowl the sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in corn syrup.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in milk, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato candy
directions: Save a small amount of powdered sugar.
Mash potato to powdered sugar until it is very stiff.
Add vanilla.
Roll in powdered sugar, very thin.
Then spread peanut butter all over it. Then roll up.
Put in refrigerator for about 20 minutes.
Then slice into small pieces. Lay on wax paper.

title: mother's grape-nut pie
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in water; set aside.
Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, butter and flavoring.
Add soaked Grape-Nuts.
Pour in unbaked shell at 350°.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ground cookies and butter in medium bowl; pat evenly on bottom and 1 inch up side of 9 inch spring form pan. Place in freezer while preparing filling.

Beat cream cheese in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed until fluffy. Beat in sugar, sour cream, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Pour mixture into prepared crust. Bake cheesecake 30 to 35 minutes or until almost set in center. Loosen cheesecake from side of pan by running a spatula between cheesecake and pan. Cool on wire rack. Refrigerate, loosely covered, 8 hours or up to 3 days. Remove side of spring form pan from cheesecake, then place on serving plate. Drizzle caramel and fudge sauces over cheesecake. Top each serving with 2 or 3 pecan halves.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer zucchini, tomatoes, peppers, onions and bread in baking pan.
Pour melted margarine over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes covered; 15 minutes uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9x13 pan.
Spread batter in pan.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Pour in margarine and cocoa.
Add flour and mix with spoon.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole delight
directions: Butter bottom
and sides of a 3 quart baking dish.
Pour asparagus
evenly
in bottom of dish.
Grate Cheddar cheese and spread evenly
on
top of asparagus layer.	Cover with peas and pimento.
In
a separate dish, dilute cream of celery soup with milk.
Add sour cream and mix.
Pour over last vegetable layer. Arrange Swiss cheese evenly for next layer.
Sprinkle on boiled eggs.
Cover with buttered crouton crumbs.	Bake in a 350° oven for about
minutes
or	until dish is bubbly and crumbs are slightly brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Keep warm in a chafing dish and serve with crackers.

title: apple dip
directions: Whip until smooth, then add peanuts.
Tastes like caramel.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large mixing bowl, soften the yeast granules in the lukewarm water, adding the sugar and salt.
When yeast has begun to bubble and foam (3 or 4 minutes), mix in the beaten egg and flour.
Mix thoroughly to form a soft dough.
Do not allow dough to rise. Immediately divide into smaller pieces and knead.
Roll and twist into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets, using a pastry brush, cover pretzels with egg wash and sprinkle salt.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° or until browned.

title: creamy wild rice soup
directions: Saute rice in oil; add water and salt.
Cook 40 minutes. Drain and reserve 1 1/2 cup stock.
Saute onion, celery and carrot in butter in Dutch oven until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour; cook over low heat 5 minutes, stir constantly.
Blend in hot chicken stock and rice stock.
Cook until slightly thickened. Add half and half, blending thoroughly.
Add rice, ham (or poultry), salt, pepper and rosemary.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: onion rice
directions: Mix soups together in casserole dish.
Stir in rice. Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jiffy clam chowder
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in soup, clams and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
If desired, sprinkle with crumbled, cooked bacon.
Serves 4 people.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add onions and blend into softened cream cheese slowly.
Add Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce and lemon juice.
Drain and rinse shrimp; shred with fork.
Blend shrimp into cheese mixture.
Add mayonnaise.
If too thick, add more mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; stir in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top of cake while still warm.
Yields one 3-layer cake.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken in melted butter and bread crumbs.
Put in casserole.
Mix soups with milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with garlic salt (pepper if you want), then cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until very warm.
Place oranges in cider whole and let float.
Keep warm in crock-pot. You may want to remove oranges after a while or drink will become bitter.
Great for holidays.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spread the apple slices in an 8-inch square cooking pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice and water over the apples.
Stir together the rest of the ingredients.
Sprinkle this mixture evenly over the apples.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: Freeze first 5 ingredients in milk jugs.
Makes approximately 2 3/4 gallons.
Remove from freezer about 5 hours prior to serving.
Mix equal part of punch base with ginger ale or Sprite. This also mixes well with champagne.

title: brown stew with herb dumplings
directions: Trim and cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Put flour and seasonings in paper bag.
Drop meat cubes into bag.
Shake meat until well covered with mixture.
Melt fat in heavy Dutch oven; add meat.
Brown all sides over low heat 10 to 15 minutes; add water.
Cover; simmer until meat is almost tender, approximately 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water if necessary; halve carrots lengthwise.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes; cover. Cook 40 to 50 minutes on low.
Add Herb Dumplings and cook as directed.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, egg and milk together and pour over butter.
Dissolve remaining sugar in peaches.
Add vanilla and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
You can alter sugar with can peaches.

title: baked chicken loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream together butter and white sugar. Cream together eggs, bananas and salt. Combine all ingredients. Put 1 spoon of batter per cookie. Flatten with fork dipped in ice water. Bake at 375° just until edges are lightly brown.
Frost with butter icing.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Use greased and floured Teflon-coated Bundt pan.

title: grandma's fruit crunch
directions: Into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put can of crushed pineapple.
Add can of cherry pie filling.
Spread over pineapple. Pour package of dry cake mix over fruit, breaking up lumps with a fork.
Sprinkle with coconut, then sprinkle almonds over all. Dribble melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: festive chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add chocolate and melt.
Turn off heat.
Add sugar, vanilla and ground nuts.
Add flour and 3 egg yolks.
Beat whites until stiff.
Mix whites into cake.
Butter 8-inch round pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: texas dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl; open chips and enjoy!

title: brownies(easy and made in one pan)
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo on stove.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan, greased and floured.
(Can sprinkle sifted powdered sugar on top after baking.)

title: velvet salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water in double boiler; cut up marshmallows.
Add to jello to dissolve.
Add cream cheese.
Let stand to congeal, then add the last 3 ingredients and pour into long baking dish.
Let stand 1/2 hour and pour 2 boxes raspberry jello which has started to congeal on top of lemon jello mixture.

title: catfish relish
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn to high and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put in jars while hot and seal.
Water bath pints 20 minutes and quarts 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip(guacamole)
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Serve with Mexican dishes or chips.

title: poppy crescents(makes 3 dozen rolls)
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 3/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
In a saucepan, combine milk, water and butter or margarine.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
(Butter or margarine need not melt entirely.) Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 times.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Divide dough into 3 equal pieces. Roll one piece out to a 12-inch circle.
Lightly brush dough with melted butter or margarine.
Cut circle into 12 pie-shaped wedges. Spoon about 2 teaspoons poppy seed filling on each wedge along the edge (opposite the point).
Beginning at the outer edge, roll wedges up tightly; seal points.
Place on greased baking sheet, point side down.
Curve to form U-shapes.
Repeat with remaining pieces of dough.
Cover loosely with waxed paper brushed with oil, then cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours

title: corned beef spread or dip
directions: Put everything in bowl, beat on medium with electric beater until mush. Can be molded or add a little milk or more sour cream for dip.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Chop jalapenos finely. Grate the cheese. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 4 cups boiling water.
Cook rice in oil in skillet until yellow, stirring constantly.
Do not brown.
Add onions and jalapeno peppers.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour bouillon over rice. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add cheese and butter. Cover. Simmer for about 10 minutes longer.

title: lye soap
directions: Heat fat.
Dissolve sugar in 1 cup cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until lukewarm.
Add this mixture to the fat. Stir until creamy.
Pour in glass baking dishes.
Cut after desired hardness is reached, usually from 12 to 36 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Heat 1 cup of water and mix sugar so it will melt.
Mix all other ingredients and freeze.
Place frozen ring in punch bowl and pour ginger ale over it.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: veal parmigiana(microwave)
directions: In a shallow dish, beat egg with salt.
Combine crumbs and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese on shallow plate or wax paper.
Cut veal into 4 serving pieces and pound to make 1/4 inch thick.
Dip veal in egg, then in crumb mixture, coating well.
Brown over Medium-high heat in oil in fry pan until golden brown, turning to brown both sides.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart (10 x 6-inch) baking dish, adding drippings from fry pan.
While meat is browning, cook onion in a small sauce dish, covered with saucer, 2 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle onion over meat in a baking dish.
Top with cheese slices, then spoon tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepper and oregano.
Cook, covered with wax paper, 6 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cook, covered, 30 seconds to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes. Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add oatmeal and dry ingredients; blend well. Bake at 350° until done in a 9 x 13 pan (greased and floured).

title: bean salad
directions: Add green pepper strips and onion to taste.
Drain beans and mix.
Pour other ingredients over beans and let set in refrigerator several hours or overnight before serving.

title: creole pork chops and rice
directions: You will need a Dutch oven or heavy pan with lid.

title: salmon loaf with cucumber-dill sauce
directions: Combine salmon, bread crumbs, milk, onion, green pepper, egg, lemon juice, celery salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Press mixture into an 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 3 minutes. Remove from pan.
Serve with Cucumber-Dill Sauce. Yields 6 servings (about 176 calories and 227 milligrams calcium per serving).

title: jane's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in hot water.
Add cold water.*
Let set at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: oman soup
directions: In Dutch oven brown meat.
Drain.
Brown onion and garlic.
Add reserved meat back into Dutch oven.
Add carrots, garbanzos, tomatoes, beef broth, water, wine, bay leaf, salt and pepper and basil.
Boil.
Then simmer 45 minutes, covered.
After 45 minutes, add ditalini.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add green beans and cook 10 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, bread and salad.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: shoney's type strawberry pie
directions: Combine water,
sugar,
and corn starch; cook until thick, approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in Jello; let it cool slightly. Slice berries into baked and cooled pie shells.
Cover with mixture.
Make sure there are plenty of berries.
Let chill several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: men's favorite congealed salad
directions: Add jello, gelatine, salt and sugar to boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Let mixture cool but not jell.
Add all of the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8.

title: chinese cabbage with beef
directions: Slice steak in thin slices; chop celery and onion.
Saute in frying pan with a little oil 3 to 4 minutes.
Add a little water to pan.
Add garlic, salt and pepper and 2 bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and let simmer, while adding the mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Let simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch.
Add the soy sauce and Gravy Master.
Then add the pea pods (just to heat through, do not cook).

title: "big mac" cookies
directions: Spread a dab of yellow frosting on top of chocolate grasshopper cookie.
Place vanilla wafer on top.
Turn upside down and spread red frosting on top of grasshopper cookie.
Place other vanilla wafer on top.
Make as many cookies as you desire.
Lay all cookies flat and brush tops with a little egg white and sprinkle with sesame seed.
They are a hit with the kids!

title: southwest skillet corn
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, saute red pepper and jalapeno in butter until tender. Add cumin; cook for 30 seconds. Add corn and cilantro; saute 2 minutes longer or until heated through. Yield: 4 servings.

title: sorghum cookies
directions: In saucepan, heat margarine, sugar and egg together.
Add sorghum and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix flour, cinnamon and soda together.
Add sugar to mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet (not too close together) and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields: 7 dozen.

title: pecan logs
directions: Sift flour, salt and 1/3 cup powdered sugar.
In mixing bowl add
shortening,
butter,
vanilla and milk;
beat well. Stir
in nuts.
Chill dough until firm.
Shape into logs about 2 inches long.
Place in ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
While warm, roll in 1 cup sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: english butter toffee
directions: Grease cookie sheets (3) with Wesson oil; set them over ice. Cook

Wash down sides of

Add 4 ounces of butter; stir

Add	salt and almonds; cook to 325°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour on
cold Wesson oiled cookie sheets, 1/4 inch thick.
Score in squares while still warm; when cold, break in pieces and allow to mellow for 24 hours.

title: barbara's chip dip
directions: Spread refried beans in dinner plate, then spread sour cream on top of beans.
Put grated cheese, olives and tomatoes on top. Eat with tortilla chips.
It's great and easy.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Blend flour, cinnamon and nuts in a bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moist.
Flour and grease 2 loaf pans; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook in stem pan for 45 minutes.

title: super party biscuits
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir constantly.

title: jello pie
directions: Line pie plate with graham crackers.
Whip the cold Pet milk real good.
Add Jell-O and sugar; whip it until it is real fluffy. Pour into pie plate and freeze.
Better to let it set in the freezer overnight and eat the next day.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press rounded tablespoonful of crumb mixture into bottom of each muffin cup.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: In large, deep pot, combine peas, water, ham shank, onions, chicken bouillon and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snackin' granola bars
directions: Toast oats in an ungreased, large, shallow baking pan in a preheated 350° oven 15 minutes.
Combine toasted oats with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together the powdered sugar and margarine; add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix well until light and fluffy.
Fill the 2 shells with this mixture; chill.
Whip cream until stiff.
Blend in well drained, crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Spoon this mixture over each pie.
Chill again.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain well.
In large bowl, combine celery, onion, mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 6 to 24 hours.

title: steamed cabbage bohemian style
directions: Steam al dente (until almost done).
Add 2 tablespoons flour, 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 tablespoons bacon grease.

title: tallarinee(from sandi conner's recipe)
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and set aside.
Saute pepper and onions in oil in a large kettle.
Add ground beef and brown well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place in casserole dishes. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: susie's forgotten chicken
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Mix rice, soup and milk. Pour into prepared dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top of chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, chestnuts, mushrooms and onion.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and soy sauce; pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss lightly.
Just before serving, add chow mein noodles and toss lightly again.
Serve immediately.
If desired, garnish with toasted almonds.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with the last four ingredients, which have been thoroughly mixed together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: When cornflakes are added, try not to stir anymore than necessary.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from sheet while hot.
A damp cloth to wipe off the edge of the spatula helps.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2 loaf pans or 18 muffin tins. Mix dry ingredients together and set aside. Grate zucchini, peel and seeds, to = 2 cups. Mix oil, sugar, honey and eggs together. Beat until pale yellow and creamy. Add vanilla, zucchini and dry ingredients together. Pour into desired pans. Bake. Cool on racks. Serves many. Can freeze. Good way to use up all that summer zucchini and share with others.

title: dear abby's pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: jen's busy day stew
directions: Mix and place in large covered casserole dish.
Cook for 5 hours in 275° oven.

title: buckeye creams
directions: Mix butter, sugar, peanut butter and cereal. Roll into balls and chill overnight.
In a double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate.
Dip balls into chocolate using toothpicks.
Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: low-fat carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins, pineapple, yogurt and cinnamon (optional) in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: Form into balls larger than golf balls the ground ham, Minute tapioca, eggs and milk.
Baste occasionally in the sauce made from the brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 12 balls.
Can be kept refrigerated or bake and cool to be reheated later.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add pudding, cinnamon and beat with electric mixer.
Add nuts, pineapple and coconut.
Bake according to box directions.
When cooled frost with cream cheese icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix sausage, Bisquick and cheese.
Use hands to knead until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni; brown hamburger.
Put onion in with hamburger. Drain hamburger and macaroni.
Mix in pan with Ragu or tomato sauce.
Put cheese on top.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bacon 'n egg pancake roll-up
directions: Prepare pancake mix and fix two 8 or 9-inch pancakes.
Cut 8 slices of bacon into pieces 1 inch long; pan-fry until browned. Drain.
Cook 8 additional slices; drain and keep warm.
Prepare favorite scrambled eggs using 6 eggs.
Just before eggs are completely cooked, stir in bacon pieces, onion and green pepper. Spread each pancake with half of egg mixture.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Serve with remaining bacon slices and, if desired, garnish with apple slices.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine salmon, onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large skillet (approximately 1/4 inch deep).
Form patties and cover outside in additional bread crumbs.
Fry in oil, turning once, until golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients to size of peas.
Sprinkle with sugar; stir in with fork.
Makes 2 singles or 1 double pie shell.

title: chocolate amaretto cake
directions: Toast almonds in oven at 350° for about 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Lightly grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over simmering water; let cool.
In a bowl, put cake pieces, then sprinkle Amaretto over and toss.
To cooled chocolate, add eggs one at a time, beating on medium speed. Stir in almond extract.
Beat heavy cream in a large bowl.
Fold chocolate and almonds into whipped cream.
Pour a thin layer of chocolate-cream mixture in bottom of pan.
Add half the cake pieces, then half the cream mixture.
Repeat.
Refrigerate until firm.
Just before serving, unmold on a plate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Try this sauce the next time you make shrimp cocktail.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except bay leaf.
Place bay leaf on top of other ingredients that has been put in casserole dish.
Place in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Discard bay leaf.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook and stir celery, red pepper and onion in margarine in skillet over medium heat until tender.
Reduce heat, add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in broccoli and pepper sauce, stirring constantly.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Roll into balls that will fit into the mushroom caps. Roll in bacon bits.
Rinse mushrooms and remove stems.
Fill each cap with a cream cheese-bacon ball.
Arrange mushrooms in a circle.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.

title: curry chicken
directions: Arrange breasts in large casserole dish; sprinkle curry, Accent and garlic powder over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until breasts stick tender. Pour barbecue sauce over breasts; place back in oven and cook another 30 minutes. May add rice after they are finished cooking.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick the cocoa, flour, sugar, salt, milk and butter; beat egg yolks and put into filling while cooking. When thick, pour in pie pan crust and let cool. Beat egg whites with 3 level tablespoons sugar and put on pie. Put in oven until brown or you can use whip cream.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Jiffy mix, cheese and milk together. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with a tablespoon. Melt oleo. Add garlic powder to oleo. Brush over biscuits when done. Bake in a 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins or chocolate chips.
Nuts are optional.
Drop rounded tablespoonful of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: glazed yeast donuts
directions: To the milk add eggs, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Then add the dissolved yeast.
Stir and begin adding flour gradually, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in flour until spongy.
Put out on floured board and form into a ball.
Put into a greased bowl.
Let rise 45 min.
Turn out again and knead.
Put back into bowl again and let rise again.
Turn out on board and knead.
Roll to 1/2 in. thick and cut 4 in. diameter circles. Small circle can be made with bottle cap.
Let rise until spongy. Cook in heavy skillet with 2 in. shortening for 1 min. each side. Cool and dip in glaze of powdered sugar, vanilla and warm milk thick enough to cling to donuts.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, salt, sugar and soda; mix well.
Add oil, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly, stirring vigorously.
Let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes. Drop mixture from spoon onto greased hot griddle.
Cook over medium heat until bubbles form on top side.
Turn and cook.
Serve with favorite syrup.
May be mixed night before and kept in refrigerator overnight.

title: shrimp scampi my way
directions: The day before, mix the cooked linguini, 3 crushed cloves of garlic, 1 tablespoon garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and 1/4 cup olive oil.
Refrigerate overnight in closed container.

title: company chicken
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oil; combine rice, salt and pepper in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Put in casserole; arrange chicken on top of rice and dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine with pumpkin mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 6 mini loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with any choice of bottled dressing.
Top with parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Cool, then add fruit and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Saut onion in margarine in a medium nonstick skillet until tender.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, 2 tablespoons shredded cheese, nutmeg and pepper; stir well.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Mix in all spices and add tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Keep in cold water until ready to use.
Combine Mozzarella cheese with cottage cheese and eggs.
Use three 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes. Make the following layers:
sauce to cover bottom of pan generously, then noodles, cottage cheese/egg mixture and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Repeat until done.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 16.

title: very tasty cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters; set aside.
Fry bacon and remove from skillet.
Add onion to bacon fat.
Saut until tender; add cabbage, bacon, salt and pepper.
Cover; let smother until done.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add lemon juice to salmon.
Combine remaining ingredients with salmon.
Spoon into a shallow buttered mold or 1-quart loaf pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown and firm. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all in skillet and cook 15 minutes or until mixture thickens and pulls away from skillet.
The peanuts begin to pop when it is almost done.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon soda. While foaming, pour onto greased platter.
Let stand 30 minutes and break into pieces.

title: apple cream pie and topping
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg, vanilla, sour cream, lemon juice and cream.
Add dry ingredients and flour over apples in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Grate raw potatoes and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon mixture, about 3 spoonfuls according to desired size, into hot oil in frying pan.
Fry until both sides are crispy.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together for 1 1/2 minutes (after mixture reaches full rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Spoon onto wax paper with a teaspoon.
Yields about 70 to 75.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: In 3-quart casserole, layer beans, chicken and water chestnuts. Mix soup, mayo and curry. Pour over layered ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly. Take from oven and top with French fried onions. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim all fat off meat and slice very thin. Combine all ingredients and marinate meat for 1 hour. Dry slightly on paper towels.
Put on oven racks. Set oven to 150° and leave door open slightly.
Let meat dry 7 to 8 hours.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Mix beans, soup and oregano in 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with French fried onions and continue baking 5 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: les' favorite pie
directions: Beat the egg whites, cream of tartar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and beat until mixed.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) buttered pie pans. Bake for 1/2 hour at 275°. Line with pecans and bake another 1/2 hour.
Melt chocolate chips, add water and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Let cool.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Add sugar/chocolate mixture mixing well.
Pour into pans and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: banana split pie
directions: Add the cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter and mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat rolls over bottom of pizza or jelly roll pan.
Bake as package directs.
Cool.
Mix all other ingredients except for vegetables and spread on crust.
Pat chopped or shredded broccoli and cauliflower into mixture on crust.
Slice carrot rounds thin and place on top of other vegetables.
This can be made up in the morning and refrigerated.
Serves 15.

title: chicken salad
directions: Separate whites from yolks of eggs.
Mash each separately with fork until fine.
Add whites to chicken and celery (and onion if desired).
Mix egg yolk with lemon juice and then mayonnaise.
Add to chicken.
Season to taste.
Serves 4 or can be used for sandwiches.

title: clam corn soup
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Add the rest of ingredients. Bring to boiling point.
Serves 4.

title: otto's onion pie
directions: Simmer onions until soft in hot butter.
Turn into pie shell. Combine 3/4 cup milk, cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend remaining 1/4 cup milk with flour; stir in cottage cheese mixture.
Mix well; pour over onions in pie shell. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Pie should be firm in center.
If desired, garnish with bacon or cooked ham.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in the rest.
Pour in cool pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in the 2 pie crusts. Bake.
I use the frozen pie crusts.

title: dipsy spread or dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate 1/2 hour or longer.
Makes 2 cups spread.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and put in 9 1/2 x 11-inch casserole.
Mix bread crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven ribs(a family favorite)
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: granny's boiled custard
directions: Bring to boil first 3 ingredients, then beat eggs and sugar well.
Add this to boiling mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir until thickened.
Add vanilla after cooling.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Have cheese at room temperature and blend all ingredients with hands. Add buttermilk or sour cream to make it thinner, if needed.

title: chocolate orange cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Combine all ingredients except egg whites including egg yolks.
Fold in whites by first adding 1/3 whites and then folding rest into lightened mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch round cake pan sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Calories:
Fat:
3 grams.

title: salty deep fried chicken(ga chein man)
directions: Prepare rice and set aside.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add chicken and coat them well.
Marinate for about 3 to 5 hours; store in refrigerator.
Deep-fry chicken until brown, about 10 minutes.
Serve hot with rice.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce. Refrigerate while preparing other fruits.
Add fruit and nuts. Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: almost perfect texas red chili
directions: Brown meat with garlic and onion in a large stew pot.
Drain excess grease, then add all the ingredients.
If serving ladies, babies, wimps or you are partial to your company, don't use the last 3 ingredients.
Let this all simmer for about 45 minutes. Take about 1/2 cup of flour and add hot water to it, a little at a time until soupy and stir into chili.
This "tightens" the chili and adds flavor.
Then simmer 15 more minutes, then serve.

title: whipped cream
directions: Beat the cream in a large chilled mixing bowl until it starts to thicken.
If you use it, gradually add the sugar and vanilla while continuing to beat.
The whipped cream is ready when it holds a stiff peak.
Be sure not to overbeat or you'll have butter.

title: goose barbecue
directions: Soak goose overnight in salt water (optional).
Place goose in pot of water (1/4 full); add dry onion flakes and celery seed. Bring to a boil, then simmer until goose is done, approximately 1 to 3 hours.
When tender, remove goose; let cool.
Take meat off bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook until soft, onions and celery.
Add rest of ingredients, stir and let simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan and date cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except shell in double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate. Garnish with whipped topping and whole pecans on top of each wedge.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles; chill thoroughly. Add noodles just before serving.
Serve on bed of lettuce, if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Beat together flour and eggs.
Stir in cottage cheese and bacon.
Place broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over broccoli. Salt to taste.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; take out.
Spread Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake another 3 minutes.

title: apple cider pound cake with caramel glaze
directions: Soften the butter.
Add the oil and then add the sugar, stirring well (10 minutes with mixer on medium).
Add the eggs one at a time, beating in between.
Add the other ingredients and beat well.
Pour in a pan (this cake is too large for a Bundt pan) and bake at 325° for 90 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while the cake is still warm.

title: tacos
directions: *Make your own taco shells by heating 4 tablespoons oil.
When oil is hot, place corn tortillas in the oil.
Fold in half until it gets to the desired hardness, turning about once or twice.

title: florida key lime pie
directions: Mix together milk, egg yolks and lime juice. Fold 1 egg white into the mixture. Pour mixture into pie shell. Beat remaining 2 egg whites; gradually add sugar and cream of tartar; add topping to pie mixture. Bake until egg whites are golden brown at 350°.

title: aunt pat's chocolate pie
directions: Mix as directed or chocolate will not absorb!!!
Melt oleo. Mix cocoa and sugar; add to the melted oleo.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Pour in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Should come out looking like a pecan pie.

title: no bake cocoa oatmeal cookie
directions: Boil milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa hard for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon on wax paper.
Cool. Fun for kids.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook in heavy sauce pan or skillet until thick.
Place in baked pie shell.
For meringue: Beat eggs and sugar until stiff.
Spoon on pie.
Place in 400 degree oven until brown.
(Watch closely.)

title: 12 hour slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onions in bowl.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar; do not mix!
Bring vinegar, oil, 2 tablespoons of sugar, celery seed and salt to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over layers; do not mix.
Chill for 12 hours or longer.
Drain to serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the shortening, butter and sugars.
Add eggs and flour.
Add soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add oats and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Bake in greased 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Beat egg yolks in a small bowl.
Add 4 tablespoons sauce to egg yolks very slowly, beating constantly.
Pour egg yolk mixture back into sauce and add 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Measure 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Set aside.
Add chicken, spaghetti and remaining sauce.
Stir well.
Spoon into a large casserole.
Pour remaining 1 1/2 cups sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (1 cup) and Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs, peel and extract until well blended. Add flour, dry ingredients and zucchini.
Beat well; stir in nuts. Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: toffee bars
directions: Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Lay graham crackers side by side (break in fourths), covering cookie sheet.
Boil butter and sugar. Boil 2 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.
Cool on foil.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put water, yeast, sugar, salt and oil in a large bowl. Add flour, a little at a time.
More flour can be added, if needed. Make a stiff dough that will roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter. Brush with melted butter.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shell and tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. In large bowl, mix macaroni, vegetables and tuna. Stir in remaining ingredients and chill thoroughly. You may add cucumber or other favorite vegetables or eliminate some of these. Makes 8 to 10 servings or 4 to 5 main dish.

title: shrimp and kraut  salad
directions: Drain the kraut well.
Boil the sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes and cool slightly.
Pour over kraut.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours.

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together thoroughly.
Form and put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon if desired and pour one 8 oz can of tomato sauce on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: corn bread(mexico)
directions: Mix as you would a cake.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: strudel dough
directions: Knead to a nice dough.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in rhubarb.
Sprinkle brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat stock until boiling.
Mix cornstarch with cold water and stir into stock.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and stir into stock.
(The eggs will look like threads.)
Add scallions and a drop of sesame oil as garnish and serve.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix all dry ingredients and put in Ziploc bag. Shake potatoes in bag and roll in melted oleo.
Pour remaining dry ingredients from Ziploc over potatoes.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.
Do not turn potatoes while cooking.

title: chicken in madeira wine(by francoise gilbert)
directions: Rinse and pat dry the chicken.
Toss with flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown chicken in heated oil until brown. Transfer to a clean bowl.
Saute thinly sliced onion and mushrooms for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add wine, scraping pieces at bottom of pan. Return chicken to pan; add cream and broth (or creamer).
Bring to boil; cook until thickened.
Spoon chicken mixture over noodles. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven, saute okra in oil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly so as not to burn.
Remove okra and set aside.
Add margarine and flour to make a roux.
Add okra and all remaining vegetables.
Cook for 5 minutes or until wilted.
Add water and worcestershire sauce. Cook for 2 hours.
Add shrimp and seasoning.
Cook for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve over cooked white rice in soup bowl.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hershey syrup cake and frosting
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift the flour and add to creamed mixture 1/2 at a time, alternating with Hershey's syrup.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical tuna sandwich
directions: Combine tuna, pineapple, celery and cream cheese; mix well. Chill, if desired, before serving.
Spread over 4 slices of bread; top with remaining bread.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: butterflied rack of lamb
directions: Marinate lamb in sauce all day.
Roast on grill.
Leave pink inside and serve with potatoes (parboiled).
Put in pan and baste in lamb marinade.
Roast in oven at 350° to 400°.

title: chocolate-cherry ring cake
directions: Stir
together	dry
ingredients.
Combine
eggs,
oil, vanilla and chocolate in another bowl.
Add to flour.
Stir in pie filling and nuts; mix well.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt or tube
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes and remove.

title: potato  soup
directions: Add this to potato mixture and let simmer for few minutes. Do Not Boil.

title: honey nut candy
directions: Boil, stirring often, to 242°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until creamy; turn on waxed paper. Separate with 2 forks.

title: twinkies cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half and lay in bottom of pan.
Layer strawberries and bananas.
Mix pudding according to directions and mix in flavoring, then pour over Twinkies and fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.
(Optional:
You can add blueberries on top or you can substitute any fruit for another.)

title: rye pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake on hot griddle.
