title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and keep refrigerated.

title: veal paprikash
directions: Season approximately 1/2 cup flour with salt and pepper. Place in paper bag.
Add veal cubes; shake, holding top of bag closed, until veal is well covered.
Add floured veal to melted butter and brown.
Stir in water, onions and paprika.
Turn down heat so that meat and gravy mixture in pan barely bubbles.
Cover and cook 2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally. Add more water if necessary to prevent sticking.
Add hot gravy slowly to sour cream, stirring to prevent curdling.
Return to skillet of meat.
Serve over mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Shape dough into small balls.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: If you have a bread machine, put all the ingredients in the bread machine and turn it on, if not mix together the ingredients, knead and set it aside.
In either case, in an hour punch down and pump it out on a floured counter and knead a bit.
Roll it out with a rolling pin until 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with butter or margarine and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll it up, moisten the edge and cut in 1 1/2 inch pieces and lay gently on a greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.
While hot drizzle with confectioners sugar moistened with water and flavored with vanilla. Eat them right away!

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear small pieces of bread dough.
Roll around in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place around in greased tube pan.
Boil oleo and brown sugar.
Pour over bread dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all fruits and nuts with graham cracker crumbs; add milk. Mix with hands.
Mixture will be thick. If too dry, you may add another orange.
Pack into 1-pound loaf pans.
Recipe makes 2 loaves.

title: sukiyaki salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients.
Blend 2 tablespoons soy sauce and garlic to taste with 1/2 cup of your favorite oil and vinegar dressing.
Toss with salad.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in vanilla.
Add eggs and beat 3 to 4 minutes. Mix together flour, salt and soda. Then add to creamed mixture.
Mixture should be sticky and dry.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by small scoops on waxed paper and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet before removing.

title: virginia peanut pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter in bowl.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen peach delight
directions: Put marshmallows and orange juice in top of double boiler over hot water until marshmallows dissolve.
Remove from heat and add peaches (smash).
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in freezing tray in refrigerator.
Freeze until very firm.
Slice and serve by itself or on top of sliced cake.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs in cup with spoon.
Add to first mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg over the berries in a large bowl.
Add creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in 8 x 8-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: effortless enchiladas
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, chiles, red pepper and sour cream.
Whisk well.
Separate and set aside 1 cup.
Mix chicken/turkey into remaining mix in medium bowl.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of mix at each end of tortilla.
Sprinkle each with cheese.
Roll up and arrange in a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold enchiladas in single layer.
Pour remaining cup of sour cream mix over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: alisha's crab dip(e-z)
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, spread cream cheese over bottom. Drain crab meat and spread over cream cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce over meat.
Dip crackers in dip and enjoy!!

title: polish stuffed cabbage(gawumki)
directions: In pot, cook 3 bags sauerkraut, 2 onions (diced), all mushrooms and butter.
Brown together and add more butter as needed.
Parboil cabbage.
Drain.
Separate each leaf.
Rinse 1 cup uncooked rice 10 times, then boil 15 minutes with approximately 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Drain well and mix with chopped meat.
Dice 3 onions and brown in butter and mix into chopped meat.
Roll into balls and wrap each in a cabbage leaf.
Place in large roasting pan you can layer.
Spread sauerkraut mixture over top.
Bake in 350° oven until meat is cooked.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar gradually.
Alternate flour and eggs.
Add flavorings.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a baking dish.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Then pour half this mixture in a buttered jelly roll pan.
Chill.
Then add Spanish nuts to the rest of the mixture and set aside.
Mix butter, vanilla pudding and evaporated milk. Boil 1 minute and add maple flavoring.
Then add powdered sugar. Mix together and spread over first layer of chocolate.
Then spread the peanut and chocolate mixture on top.
Cool and cut.

title: yvonne's spinach with garlic and lemon
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon of oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic and cook, stirring constantly for 20 seconds.
Add spinach by handfuls, tossing the leaves in the skillet until all of it fits. Cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and toss in the remaining oil and lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Divide among 4 plates and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: "kreatopita" - meat pita
directions: Dice onions fine; place in pan with a little water and boil for 10 minutes until limp.
Drain water off and add ground meat to onions in the pan, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook mixture, stirring it continuously for 15 to 20 minutes until meat is cooked.
Take pan off the fire and allow mixture to cool slightly. Beat eggs and add to warm meat; add milk and mix.

title: strawberry cream dip
directions: Rinse strawberries and pat dry with paper towel; set aside. Whisk remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour dip into a bowl. Set bowl in center of a platter.
Arrange strawberries around platter.

title: chocolate covered pecan halves
directions: Place chocolate chips and almond bark in bowl. Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until melted.
Pour in pecan halves and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls out onto waxed paper.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and refrigerate until partially thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate until set.

title: tropical cookie bars
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix flour, butter, 1/4 cup almonds and 1/4 cup sugar. Mix until crumbly. Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: If you would like you can use or add onion, green peppers, ripe or black olives and chopped up pickles.
Or, top each one with ripe or black olives.

title: coffee cake muffins
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Add the milk, egg and oil and mix.
The batter should not be smooth. Spoon into greased muffin tins about 1/2 to 2/3 full.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add yeast to lukewarm water and add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add salt, shortening and remaining sugar to milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 3 cups flour.
Beat well. Add enough more flour to make thick dough.
Cover bowl and let rise about double in bulk.
Shape into loaves or rolls and place in oven.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Combine sugar, oil, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; beat until blended.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Using 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie, shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Place balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, roll again in powdered sugar.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare the 3 flavors of gelatin separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine the lemon gelatin, sugar and remaining 1 cup boiling water; stir until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until thickened.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake pie shell.
Beat eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Combine cheeses, flour and crab.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over pie shell. Pour cream mixture over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bird's nest
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. (You may want to double if you use more eggs.) Add diced egg whites.

title: cheri's juice
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with fresh orange slices.
Easy to make for large groups.

title: taco dip and chips
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. When ready to serve, top with lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Remove the outer crust from bread slices and cut into bite size squares.
Cut enough slices to cover the bottom of the baking dish.
Cut cream cheese into small chunks and spread over the bread pieces.
Place enough of the cut up bread pieces on top to cover cheese chunks.
The dish should be full, but not overfull.
(You may not necessarily use the entire loaf.)
Combine eggs, milk, syrup and cinnamon-sugar; use wire whip until blended.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes. If toast browns too quickly, re-cover and continue baking.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion and garlic (optional).
Drain. Then add cans of beans (do not drain).
Add taco mix, salad dressing, tomatoes, tomatoes and chilies, water and corn.
When all ingredients are combined, cook over medium heat for at least 30 minutes.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Stir together mustard, mayonnaise and honey.
Add in paprika. Blend with spoon until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: holiday gift cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Combine remaining flour with cherries and nuts.
Fold into the batter.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit.
Add sugar.
Let set two hours or longer. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add Ro-Tel and tomato sauce.
Simmer together.
Layer all ingredients starting with crushed chips and ending with cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: pimiento dip
directions: Combine and mix until well blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: zela's baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine or butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chicken breasts very liberally with seasoning salt on one side.
Turn over in melted margarine and sprinkle this side. Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Juice is great over mashed potatoes.
Serve homemade biscuits with this.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Drain bacon; set aside and save 1/2 cup fat.
Saute onion; add vinegar and sugar and boil for a few minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise with wire whisk.
Add bacon.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat only what you need at one time.
Heat in microwave.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Place grated cheese in bowl. Add margarine. Let come to room temperature. Add flour, cereal and red pepper. Mix together to make a dough. Pinch small amount and press to make cookie. Place 1/4 of a nut on top and bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until bottom is light brown.

title: mary ellen's orange punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Float cherries, strawberries, limes, oranges or lemon rinds.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with eggs, milk and ginger.
Cream together butter, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and brown sugar.
Add to potato mixture.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Top with 1 package small marshmallows.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: date nut cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and dates.
Place 1/4 cup nuts and 1/4 cup dates in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Pour mixture over nuts and dates.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with a medium container of Cool Whip, 1/4 cup nuts and 1/4 cup dates.

title: baked hot dogs
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Boil slowly for 2 or 3 minutes. Split hot dogs; place in shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey crackle
directions: Melt butter on low heat, add sugar and honey; stir until melted, then let it boil slowly for 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from fire, add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, mix well and spread in large oiled pan and put it in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: danish potato salad with dill
directions: Wash potatoes.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and let cool slightly.
Peel only if skins are tough.
Cut potatoes into thin slices.

title: tangy chops and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put half the salt and pepper on chops and brush with 2 tablespoons of the dressing.
Mix cabbage and carrot together in a baking dish.
Sprinkle on remaining salt and pepper.
Pour on remaining dressing.
Toss. Spread evenly over the bottom.
Place chops on top.
Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pork and apple pie
directions: Cook bacon in an ovenproof 12-inch skillet until crisp. Remove to paper towels to drain.
In drippings, saute onions until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Dust pork lightly with flour. Brown a third at a time in drippings.
Add oil if needed.
Remove from the heat and drain.
To pork, add bacon, onions, apples, sage, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Stir in cider and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until pork is tender. In saucepan, cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and mash with milk and 3 tablespoons butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove skillet from oven and spread potatoes over pork mixture.
Melt butter and brush over potatoes.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes or until brown.
Serves 10.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl.
Decorate with an ice mold that has fruit inside.

title: lime jello cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Grease and lightly flour bottom only of a tube pan.
Dissolve lime Jell-O and hot water.
Sift in
bowl white
cake
mix.
Make a well and add Jell-O mixture plus Wesson
oil
and
eggs.
Add one at a time, stir after each. Pour
into
pan and bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Stir in bowl powdered sugar and juice of 2 lemons.
Mix well.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Drizzle glaze over it.

title: nut scotchies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and add soda and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well. Stir in rolled oats and chopped nuts.
Drop from a level tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pickups
directions: Shells:
Mix all ingredients for shells until smooth. Refrigerate and chill while making filling.
Divide into 24 balls and press into small muffin tins, making shells, being careful not to make any holes or filling will stick.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Pick and wash beans.
Cover with cold water; let stand 2 hours.
Add enough cold water to come to about 3 inches over beans.
Add ham bone and fat, celery, onion and carrots.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 2 hours.
More hot water can be added during cooking.
About 20 minutes before end of cooking, add salt, garlic powder and pepper to taste.
The key to taste is to allow liquid to thicken slightly.
A can of tomatoes can be added in the last 20 minutes, also.

title: baked ham
directions: Turn oven on to 475° and let it get hot.
Wrap ham in heavy aluminum foil and pour the coke over it before sealing the aluminum foil.
Reduce the oven to 200° and place the ham in and bake overnight.

title: crisco single crust
directions: Mix as for double crust.
Press dough into a flat circle with smooth edges.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to a circle, about 1 1/2-inches larger than inverted pie plate.
Be careful not to stretch the dough.
Trim 1/2-inch beyond edge of plate.
Fold under to make a double thickness of dough around rim and flute with fingers or fork.

title: sloppy joes for 50
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Cook onion until transparent.
Add flour.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Simmer for one hour.

title: apple ginger coffee cake
directions: With an electric mixer on medium speed, mix together the flour, salt, cinnamon, brown sugar, ginger root, white sugar and canola oil.
Take 2 cups of this mixture out and reserve for the crumble topping.
To the remainder, add the baking soda, baking powder, eggs and buttermilk.

title: washday dinner
directions: Use a large, flat pan, enamel or aluminum.
Melt butter in it. Slice a thick layer of onions, then a generous layer of potatoes. Sift flour over this.
Pour tomatoes (use a large can if for large family) over; slice sausages thinly and cover the top.
Cover with boiling water salted to taste and bake slowly 3 hours.
If sausages get too brown, turn them over.
This recipe is so tasty that it will not be confined to washdays if once tried.

title: amber chicken
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Pour over chicken wings and soak overnight for 4 to 6 hours. Bake 1 hour and baste with sauce while cooking.

title: graham cracker cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Press
into
9-inch
pie pan, saving 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: veal cutlet in cream
directions: Mix mustard, ginger, pepper, salt and flour together.
Pound into veal cutlets.
Brown on both sides in butter in skillet; add cream.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and let stand at least overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:	Place tomato paste, tomato sauce, pepper, oregano, basil leaves and garlic powder into saucepan.
Saute onion in vegetable oil; put into the sauce then brown hamburger and place into the sauce.
Cook sauce for 30 minutes.
In another pan boil water with 1 teaspoon vegetable oil.
After water comes to a boil, place 1 package lasagna noodles and cook until tender.
Cut with a fork.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix all the first dry ingredients in a bowl. Stir in milk and melted shortening. Add nuts. Turn into a greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Pour hot water over entire batter. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Serve warm plain or with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
(May not wish to use all of stuffing mix.) Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add eggs; stir well.
Add raisins and margarine in bits over top of pudding.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Scald milk until bubbles form around edge; remove from heat. Add sugar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Stir in half and half, vanilla, whipping cream and peanut butter.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Freeze as directed.

title: mae's apple pie
directions: Mix seasonings with apples except for butter and lemon.
Pour into pie crust.
Put butter slices on top of apples.
Squeeze lemon on top.
Cover with pie crust and seal around edges.
Prick with fork and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Put foil strips around edge of pie for first 20 minutes, then remove.
Cook at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in an 11 x 14 pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° until done.

title: buckeyes
directions: Knead all ingredients well.
Form into balls, about 1-inch. Melt one 12 ounce package chocolate chips and 1/3 stick of paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls with toothpick and place on waxed paper to harden.

title: baked salmon
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Place salmon fillets or salmon steaks in greased Pyrex flat dish.
Cover with thin sliced tomatoes and onions and brush with olive oil mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coca-cola chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 11 x 17-inch pan.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Melt butter and Coca-Cola together.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Add the liquid to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
The batter will be very thin.
Pour into the prepared pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: quick sweet and sour beets
directions: Drain beets and reserve syrup.
Mix syrup and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in beets and orange slices or pineapple.
Heat through.

title: chicken chili corn casserole
directions: In 2-quart ungreased casserole, place 2 cups chip. Top with corn. Add chicken and olives. Mix soup, chili, sour cream, salt and cumin. Spread over chicken mixture. Sprinkle with remaining chips. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. When done, sprinkle with grated cheese and melt under broiler (optional)

title: taco pie
directions: Melt oleo, add milk and 2 tablespoons taco seasoning mix.
Stir in instant potato mix.
Press mixture over bottom and up sides of 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining taco mix, beans and barbecue sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Turn into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with sour cream.

title: potato and hot dogs for pressure cooker
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put in pressure cooker.
Slice hot dogs; add to cooker.
Slice onion; add to taters.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and a little parsley.
Pour over taters.
Bring up pressure.
Cook for 7 to 8 minutes after control jiggles.

title: rosettes
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Mix milk, vanilla, sugar, salt and
egg
together.
Stir
slowly
into flour, then beat until smooth
with rotary or electric beater at medium speed. Makes about
rosettes.
Heat
iron,
then dip hot mold in batter then
back
into pan of fat.
Fry at 365° until brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Ice with egg white icing.
Beat egg whites until
stiff.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Frost. Can add food coloring.
Bake Rosettes with icing for 1 hour at 150° to dry.
Then store in airtight container.

title: green beans with a twist
directions: In a skillet, saute the beans and mushrooms in butter. Sprinkle with dressing mix; toss to coat.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple crisp(microwave recipe)
directions: Place apples in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Microwave at High (100%) until apples are tender-crisp, 2 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Set apples aside.

title: * frankfurter casserole *
directions: Cut franks in half, lengthwise and then crosswise; set aside. Melt butter in heavy skillet (be sure handle is ovenproof).
Add half of onions and cook slowly until soft.
Add green beans (do not defrost).
Add other half of onions.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and marjoram, mixing well.
Fold in frankfurters and heat to bubbling.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in water until crisp, but tender.
Drain. Layer broccoli and cauliflower, separated into florets, in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turtle a la king
directions: Mash egg yolks and blend with softened butter.
Heat cream in the top of a double boiler.
Gradually mix in egg yolks.
Add seasonings and turtle meat and cook 15 minutes until thickened. Serve over toast or in patty shells.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing by the directions on the package. Prepare all other ingredients as shown, placing all in fairly large bowl.
Pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots and cauliflower in boiling water (salted) 4 minutes.
Drain and combine with onions, green pepper and mushrooms in a large bowl.
Pour French dressing over the vegetables and mix.
Cover and allow to marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: cool and easy strawberry pie for diabetics
directions: Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl and stir until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water with ice cubes to make 1 cup. Add to Jell-O, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups of Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Mix in chopped strawberries.
Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thick and will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip and strawberry halves.
Serves 8.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Make paste of food coloring, vanilla and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Add alternately the cake flour and buttermilk.
Fold in baking soda mixed with vinegar.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 2 quart container.
Add ginger ale.
Real good.

title: bar cheese
directions: Melt oleo and Velveeta cheese in double boiler or microwave. Remove from heat and add cream cheese, sour cream, onion juice, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Add yellow food coloring and 1 drop of red to desired color.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in fat.
Add rest of ingredients except meat.
Simmer slowly for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add meat; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburg or hot dog buns.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops, then simmer with the rest of ingredients until done.
Serve with a Cajun dish, sauteed okra, butter beans, corn and tomatoes.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer meat, carrots, onion and potatoes.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over vegetables and meat. Cover casserole dish and bake in 300° oven for 4 hours.

title: mexican style cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Cut steak into thin strips, approximately one-inch long and saute along with onion and celery in the butter.
Add mushrooms and vegetables, soy sauce and water to mixture.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or dried Chinese noodles.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper on top.
Dot with butter.
Cover; bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes (or until tender).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup or honey and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes or to a hard boil.
Add vanilla and soda.
Mix with popped popcorn.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container to keep crisp.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Grind vegetables and mix with salt.
Let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Blend sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix with ground vegetables.
Store in refrigerator or fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot, about 10 minutes.

title: christmas cherry salad
directions: Juice and water make 2 1/2 cups; cook juice and jello until dissolved.
Add all ingredients.
Chill!

title: pork or beef filling for pocket bread
directions: You can add 1 crushed garlic clove and 1 cup chili sauce, if desired.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Butter 8 x 10-inch pan.
Line with tortillas.
Cook hamburger meat until done.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture and 1/2 of grated cheese, then more tortillas, then the rest of meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 400° until the cheese melts.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Cook pineapple for 3 minutes.
Add jello and cook 2 minutes. Remove.
Mix cream cheese.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13
x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine chicken pieces, celery,
rice, onion and peas in a	large bowl.
Stir in
mayonnaise,
lemon	juice,	salt
and pepper; mix well.
Melt butter	in
medium
size saucepan over medium
heat. Stir in flour.
Cook,
stirring
constantly,
1 minute or until mixture is	thickened
and	bubbly.
Gradually pour in chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and smooth, about 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture; stir to thoroughly combine.
Spoon into prepared pan. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: berry cake
directions: Mix everything in order except berries.
Clean berries and dry them.
Toss in a little flour and fold into mix.
Bake in 2 square or 3 round pans.

title: chili casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, mix ground beef, onion, seasoning mix, tomato sauce and water.
Heat for 15 minutes.
In a greased 9 x 9-inch casserole, layer meat, beans, chips, olives and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and casserole is hot.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix vegetables and toss with Italian dressing or oil and vinegar.
Add Italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese and toss. Crunchy and good tasting; healthy, too!

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with Cheddar cheese and picante sauce.
Crunch and add a bag of Doritos.
Brown ground beef.
Add drained beans and 1/4 teaspoon salt to ground beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix into cold salad.

title: oven lasagne
directions: Brown beef; drain. Add sauce, water and salt. Bring to boil. Layer sauce, uncooked lasagne noodles, Ricotta and Mozzarella. Repeat layers ending with sauce. Top with Parmesan. Cover tightly. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream butter and sugar and beat well. Add flour and cornstarch beating until smooth. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes (they do not brown). Cool slightly, remove to wire rack and cool. Add frosting to top. Yields 8 to 9 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mash butter and crackers.
Put 1/2 cracker mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Layer chicken, chestnuts, crackers, chicken and chestnuts.
Pour in mixtures of soups and sour cream.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked crispy chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Dip in Pet milk.
Roll in mixture of corn flakes, Accent, salt and pepper.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan lined with Reynolds Wrap.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: white snow snack
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave until smooth. Mix all other ingredients in bowl and cover with melted chocolate. Mix chocolate through and place in chunks on wax paper to dry. Enjoy!

title: sole veronique(preparation time:  5 minutes.  cooking time:  2 minutes.)
directions: Place fish fillets in a 9-inch non-metallic pie plate.
In a small bowl, stir together wine, lemon juice, lemon peel, pepper and grapes.
Spoon over fish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until fish turns opaque.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: beef stock
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a 12-quart pot.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
About 20 minutes after the stock starts to cook, fat will start to rise to the surface.
Skim this fat off with a spoon.
After all the fat is removed, add 4 to 5 bay leaves and continue to cook.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix ingredients; let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Great for fish, chicken, onion rings, etc.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in large container.
For 1 serving, put 1/4 to 1/3 cup in cup and add hot water.
Stir.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer, add condensed milk and stir well.
Add dairy milk to fill line on freezer and stir.
If fruit is used, add before dairy milk.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen, carrots, celery and broth and when done, remove meat from bones and set aside.
Using can of soup, add to broth.

title: red christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and pineapple juice.
Add sherbet and pour Sprite over sherbet.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in quiche dish.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine chocolate and 3 tablespoons water in saucepan.
Heat until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold gently into whipped cream.
Spoon into meringue pie shell. Chill for 2 hours or longer.
Garnish with additional stiffly whipped cream, shaved bitter chocolate and nuts.

title: baked apples(lenten recipe)
directions: Core apples and pare
the
upper half.	Place in baking dish. Fill the core well with
1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon shortening.
Sprinkle
tops
with pinch of cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour hot water
or orange juice with water around the apples and seal pan with
foil.
Bake	in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil to
baste
apples.
Cover
to	complete baking
for
20 minutes more.
Serve
hot
or
cold
with
pan juices.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Make 1-crust pie shell and bake.
Dissolve 1 package of frozen unthawed sweetened sliced strawberries (16 ounces).
Break up berries in hot gelatin until gelatin thickens.
When partially set, pour into cooled pie shell.
Garnish with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: italian caponata
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add eggplant and next 5 ingredients. Saute 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in vinegar, garlic, basil and oregano.
Cook an additional 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve with grilled pork or poultry. Yields 3 1/2 cups (6 calories and 15% fat per tablespoon).
Protein 0.2, fat 0.1 (saturated fat 0), carbohydrate 1.2, fiber 0.3, cholesterol 0, sodium 3.

title: punch
directions: Put sherbet in bowl. Add punch and ginger ale. Mix and serve immediately.

title: super jello salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and undrained pineapple.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch pan until set.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with coffee. Stir until smooth, then set aside.
In small bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Add heavy cream and beat mixture until it mounds slightly.
Beat in chocolate mixture until well blended.
Spoon into serving bowls and top with whipped cream.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake as directed in rectangular pan.
Remove from oven, and using fork, punch full of holes.
Pour can of cream of coconut and can of Eagle Brand milk over top.
Let cool, then cover with Cool Whip and frozen coconut, thawed.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and let drain.
Place in slow cooker the picante sauce.
Add beef and cheese.
Let cook until you are ready to serve.
Dip with tortillas.

title: fiesta beef kabob
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients (except meat) along with 1/2 cup of water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Cool.
Add meat; toss to coat.
Refrigerate overnight (or at least 6 hours).
Drain meat; reserve marinade.
Thread meat on skewers. Broil over medium coals 20 to 25 minutes, turning once and brushing with marinade 2 or 3 times.
Serves 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls into deep fat.

title: blueberry griddle cakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Add butter and blueberries; mix lightly. Bake on lightly greased and moderately hot griddle. Serves 6.

title: strata
directions: Cut donut shaped bread using donut cutter - no crusts.
Fit leftover scraps into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer cheese on bread.
Sprinkle on ham and broccoli.
Arrange donut-shaped bread on top in two rows, down either side of center.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread, saturating each donut.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
For color add cherry tomatoes and/or sprig of parsley in each donut center.

title: rhubarb-lemonade punch
directions: Makes approximately
1	gallon.
Clean	rhubarb and cut into cubes.
Add
sugar, water and lemonade.
Stir, then cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until very soft.	Drain off juice and chill.
Just
before
serving, pour mixture over ice cubes or ice ring
in
punch
bowl.
Pour carbonated beverage (desired amount) carefully down side of bowl.
Serve.

title: aaron's texas queso
directions: Chop up the Velveeta and Monterey Jack cheese into cubes and place into a crock-pot.
Add the Ro-Tel tomatoes, milk and jalapenos.
Stir occasionally and cover.
Takes about an hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put boneless chicken breasts in baking dish.

title: multi-grain, low-cal pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix in egg and oil.
Add enough skim milk to make batter pourable.
Cook on griddle at medium heat, turning once when bubbles appear.
Makes six 4-inch pancakes, about 55 calories each.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts, then the coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed. Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter; remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Drizzle evenly over cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain. Cook rice.
Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Mix broccoli, rice, soup and sauteed onion together.
Add a little of the Cheez Whiz (about 1/3 jar) and mix.
Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Pour into buttered casserole dish and spoon remaining Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, then add flour and milk.
Add flavoring last.
Pour into 2 pans and cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: kay's ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in half and return bottom half to pan. Put a layer of ham and then a layer of cheese on rolls. Mix margarine, mustard, worcestershire sauce and onion powder together. Drizzle a small amount over cheese and save rest for topping. Add top half of rolls. Brush or spoon over the top of the rolls the remaining margarine mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. May need to cover lightly with foil to keep tops from getting to brown. May refrigerate after fixing and bake just before serving.

title: cream puffs
directions: First, bring water and butter to a boil; add flour.
Cook until thick; cool.
When cool, add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Drop from spoon onto a greased pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut open.
Fill with favorite pudding.

title: oven dill pickles
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Pack pickles and dill into jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon alum to a quart.
Pour boiling mixture over pickles.
Put jars on grate.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Do not tighten lids until you remove from oven.
Ready to eat when cold.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine
salmon,
salt,
dry
milk and pepper.
Stir in onion, eggs, bread and blend well.
Then stir in hot water and butter. Press
mixture
into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until knife inserted near center comes out
clean.
Bake about 1 hour.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: chocolate chip brownie pie
directions: Cut 5 cookies in half; set aside.
Finely roll remaining cookies.
Combine cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine, press on bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan.

title: the munchie spinach
directions: Combine spinach, butter and cream cheese in an ovenproof dish. Place a layer of artichoke hearts over the top.
Combine Ritz crackers and Parmesan cheese; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven (or until brown on top).

title: sheila's irish bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and if desired, caraway seed.
Set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar.
Add egg, buttermilk and dry ingredients.
After blended, add raisins. Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix onion, soup and sour cream.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Save enough cheese to sprinkle on top.
Add frozen potatoes.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In a saucepan bring 4 cups water to a boil.
Add rice and stir.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Heat butter in a large skillet over medium high heat.
Brown chicken in butter and season with salt to taste.
Set chicken aside.
Transfer cooked rice to the skillet in which the chicken was cooked, stirring to brown.
In a separate skillet, scramble eggs.
To the rice add chicken, mushrooms, green onions, eggs and soy sauce to taste.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
You can add Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pasta, shrimp or tuna, bell pepper, carrots and zucchini.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; toss lightly to combine.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: mary ann's new england clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add all other ingredients except light cream.
Cook until potatoes are done, then add light cream. Good chowder-!

title: chess pie
directions: Put sugar in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oleo.
Cream until light.
Add milk and mix.
Add corn meal and vanilla; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: tex-mex soup
directions: Brown meat with onion in a medium-sized pot; drain well. Drain and chop tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add tomatoes and juice to saucepan with beans, tomato sauce, water, picante sauce and cumin.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Top with tortilla chips, lettuce and sour cream, as desired.
Makes about 10 to 12 cups.

title: creamy microwave fudge
directions: Grease an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, milk, butter and salt in a 3-quart microwave bowl.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave on High 4 minutes or until mixture begins to boil.
Uncover and microwave on High 10 minutes longer, stirring every 3 minutes.
Continue to microwave 8 minutes longer, stirring every 2 minutes, until mixture thickens slightly and rises less when stirred.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla, stirring until marshmallows and chocolate chips are melted.
Add nuts, stirring vigorously, until mixture is creamy and slightly glossy.
Spread in prepared pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: cheesy chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt margarine and cook the zucchini, carrots, celery, onions, garlic and oregano about 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add soups, milk and water, stirring until well blended.
Stir in chicken and pepper sauce.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and polish sausage in white wine
directions: In a large skillet or wok, saute the sausage and chicken breasts in the olive oil until lightly browned.
Add bell pepper, onions, mushrooms and garlic and continue to saute.
Add seasoning and continue to saute until chicken appears to be getting done.
Add white wine; cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Add tomato and simmer for three to five minutes.
If thickening is needed for sauce, stir in cornstarch mixture of one tablespoon in one-fourth cup water, in an amount that will cause a light thickening of sauce.
Serve with almond slivered rice, salad and any green vegetable.

title: christmas sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla, water and nuts. Add flour and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when still a little warm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small pan, heat oil; add onion and pepper.
Saute 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam sauce, bread crumbs and cheese.
Put mixture into oven-safe casserole dish.
Cover and bake 20 minutes (when cheese is melted).
Serve warm with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk in small mixing bowl.
Measure 2 cups of the prepared whipped topping; set aside.
Add 1 cup of the milk and chocolate pie filling mix to remaining topping in bowl.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add mushrooms and saute 3 minutes. Add chicken, cream, salt and pepper.
Heat to almost boiling.
In a small bowl, make a smooth paste from flour and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir into the chicken mixture and stir until the sauce is smooth and slightly thickened.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread spaghetti on bottom of buttered 8-inch square pan.
Layer the Mozzarella cheese over the chicken, working the first layer of slices down into the chicken mixture a little.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese slices.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on last. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake and icing
directions: Combine flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and sugar.
Mix oleo, oil, water and cocoa in pan and bring to boil.
Add flour mixture while hot.
In separate bowl, beat soda and buttermilk.
Add vanilla and eggs, well beaten.
Add other mixture and mix well.
Pour into large cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together shortening and peanut butter.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Make into balls the size of hickory nuts and press top with fork.
Bake in hot oven.

title: president's chicken
directions: Mix all but breasts on low heat in skillet until melted.
Put in breasts and cook over low 30 to 35 minutes with lid on. (Shorten cooking time by microwaving 3 minutes and cook 15 to 20 minutes.)

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured coffee can.
Fill 4 cans half full, then cook at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool.

title: larry's tapioca pudding
directions: Separate the egg yolks from the whites. Mix in heavy bottomed pan the salt, 3/4 cup sugar, tapioca, egg yolks and milk. Mix, then cook, bringing it to a boil.
STIR CONSTANTLY. Cool slightly and add vanilla.

title: lemonade
directions: You will need a big pot and 1 bag of ice for this recipe.

title: blackberry crunch
directions: Combine berries, juice, water, flavoring, sugar and cinnamon. Bring to boil.
Add cornstarch.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, pour dry mix out of box.
Spread evenly. Place sliced margarine over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, water, flour, oil and sour cream. Beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup chocolate chips on top.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle 1/2 of the cinnamon sugar mixture on top. Pour rest of batter on top.
Then sprinkle with rest of the chocolate chips and cinnamon sugar.
Bake 35-40 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon-poached halibut
directions: In a large, nonstick frying pan over medium heat, saute the onion in the oil until transparent, about 5 minutes.
Add stock; bring to a boil.
Add lettuce; cook until it starts to wilt, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the lemon juice and pepper.
Add the fish and cook until just firm to the touch, about 5 minutes.
Carefully drain the excess liquid from the pan into a 2-quart saucepan.
Over high heat, cook until reduced by half, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: orange cranberry trifle
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 tsp. orange extract with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping and cranberry sauce.
Set aside.
Arrange 1/3 of the cake slices on bottom of 8 inch square dish.
Mix milk, vanilla and 1/2 tsp. orange extract.
Drizzle approximately 2 Tbsp. of milk mixture over cake slices.
Spread 1/3 of cream cheese mixture over cake slices.
Repeat for second and third layers, using remaining cake slices, milk and cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds and cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 or up to 24 hours, before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend liquid ingredients and add to the dry.
Roll out thin for crackers or thicker for bread. Bake for 15 minutes at 325° on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix together and place in ice cream freezer.
Freeze about 15 to 20 minutes in electric freezer or until difficult to turn in hand-turn freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add nuts, zucchini and coconut last.
Bake at 350° in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer except chocolate chips.
Beat high speed, 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in tube pan.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potato slices and packet of seasoned sauce mix into ungreased, 2-quart dish.
Then add tomatoes, water and oregano.
Stir this real good.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cherry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together until well blended.
Chill and serve.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and marinate with soy sauce, sherry, ginger, cornstarch, sugar and garlic powder.
In skillet, add oil.
Cook mushrooms and green onions until tender.
Remove. Add chicken and marinade and cook.
Return mushrooms and onions to pan.
Now add peas and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: linzer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Chop almonds finely.
Mix all but 2 tablespoons flour with both sugars, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender.
With a fork, mix in the almonds, egg and egg yolk.
Remove 1/2 cup dough and add the reserved flour to it.
Knead well and chill until firm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and lightly press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let crust cool completely.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla, mayonnaise and cold water.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: all-in-one-breakfast(mix the night before)
directions: Mix well the milk, eggs and salt.
Place muffins, cut side up, into an oblong baking dish.
Pour milk and egg mixture over and spread cheese on top.
Cover well and place in refrigerator overnight (12 to 24 hours).

title: potato crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine milk, margarine and potatoes; cook and stir over low heat just until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat and pour in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours. Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about one hour.
Punch down and divide into thirds.

title: cheese ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
40 minutes.

title: elegant and frozen chocolate cream pie
directions: Crust:
Crush chocolate wafers finely to make 1 1/2 cups of crumbs.
Combine with melted margarine and press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: miniature meat balls
directions: Mix and form 1-inch balls.
Fry in a small amount of shortening.
Simmer in sauce after frying:

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes(microwave)
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each tomato.
With small spoon or melon baller, scoop out pulp.
Discard pulp and tops of tomatoes.
Place tomatoes cut side down on paper towel to drain. Combine remaining ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Mix well. Stuff tomatoes with cheese mixture.
Arrange tomatoes on paper towel-lined plate with smaller tomatoes in center.
Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture is hot, rotating plate once.
Sprinkle tomatoes lightly with snipped fresh parsley, if desired.

title: cream cheese appetizer
directions: Mix the jelly with the horseradish (or to suit your taste). Pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: cheesy squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix
the
cream
cheese
ingredients and spread over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Split chili peppers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Spread in a single layer in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese, green onions and 1 1/2 cups of Mozzarella over chiles.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, flour and salt together until smooth. Pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in custard comes out clean.

title: baklava(nut-filled pastry)
directions: Make syrup by boiling water, 4 c. sugar and lemon over low heat until it begins to thicken or when mixture reaches 220 degrees with a candy thermometer.
Cool slightly.
Warm the rendered butter to liquid state.
Combine walnuts and 3/4 c. sugar and set aside.
Brush butter onto sides and bottom of jelly roll pan.
Place pastry sheet on bottom of pan and brush with butter. Keep remainder of dough covered with damp cover.
Repeat process until there are 25 layers of buttered dough (or 1 box).
Spread nut mixture evenly over dough. Place a leaf pastry over nut mixture and butter.
Finish with remaining layers.
With a sharp knife, cut dough with nut mixture into diamond shapes.
Add more rendered butter on top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Remove from oven, let cool 20 minutes and drizzle with cool syrup.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl, whisk mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, oranges, onion, bacon and raisins.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Yield:
10-12 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Put flour and salt in bowl.
Mix milk and oil, then combine with flour.
Stir with fork until ball forms.
Split in half. Roll between wax paper on damp counter.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Add flour. Mix well.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Roll in more flour to about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Fill with desired filling.
Fold two opposite corners together.
Leave other two corners flat.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: date nut balls
directions: Put dates, butter and sugar in boiler on low heat.
Cook until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Roll in small balls, then roll in coconut.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pinch angel food cake into pieces in a long pan.
In bowl combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Add milk. Pour mixture over cake.
Slice strawberries on top.
Spread strawberry glaze on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs lightly with fork.
Add all other ingredients, except butter.
Add melted butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add broccoli until it can be well mixed.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Fry the potatoes in 3 tablespoons oil until they are medium-soft, but not soft.
Also fry hamburger, then mix together all but the cheese.
Put in a cake pan.
Cover and bake in slow oven for about an hour.
Add the cheese when almost done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes to just done stage. Melt cheese over low heat. Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: beef tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Fill each taco shell with 2 tablespoons meat and place tacos on baking sheet.
Bake in oven 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not use toast, broil or top brown settings.

title: brownies
directions: Bring the margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over the sugar, flour and soda. Add the eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour onto a foil lined jelly roll pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli and onion together. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over vegetables in large bowl with seal proof lid.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: roasted peking chicken
directions: Place a pot containing 3 quarts of water over high heat.
When the water comes to a boil, lower the chicken into the water (it should be completely immersed).
Cook the chicken for about a total of 10 minutes. (It will take about 5 minutes for the water to return to the boil, and the chicken should cook for an additional 4 or 5 minutes at a gentle boil.)
Drain the chicken and place it, on a rack, uncovered, in the refrigerator, for 5 to 6 hours, or overnight.
The skin should be somewhat dry at this point.
(The drier the skin, the crispier it will be after cooking.)

title: fast and easy tacos
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in large frying pan.
Add chilies, tomatoes, lemon juice, cumin and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer uncovered 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat shells according to package directions.
Fill shell with taco mixture.
Top with sauce, sour cream, cheese and lettuce.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, Rice Krispies and coconut, in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes 60 balls.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar together; heat to dissolve the sugar. Add everything together.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sweet and hot mustard
directions: Mix mustard and cider vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, beat eggs and add sugar; continue to beat. Add this mixture to mustard and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into clean jars and refrigerate.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes the water, cloves and cinnamon; strain. Add and simmer the tea bags.
Add the orange juice, lemonade and additional water as specified on juice cans.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Allow to cool. Spread cooked mixture over congealed gelatin.

title: bunsteads
directions: Bake at 250° for 30 minutes (wrap in aluinum foil).

title: ground beef soup
directions: Place beef and onion in skillet and fry until done.
Drain. Place in a heavy saucepan and add desired vegetables, cover with water and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato juice and season with 1 teaspoon each salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Place the cooked, drained spaghetti in a large greased casserole dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix beaten egg and milk; pour over spaghetti.
Spread drained and browned ground beef over spaghetti. Pour the spaghetti sauce evenly over spaghetti mixture.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart casserole.
Loosely cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Uncover.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until hard ball stage (for hard ball stage, drop a few drops of mixture in cold water and it will form a hard ball).
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating on high.
Add vanilla. Continue to beat 4 to 5 minutes until candy shape.
Add nuts. Quickly drop by teaspoons onto wax paper or pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Yields 1 pound.

title: potato salad
directions: Fry the bacon lightly, remove from fat and crumble.
Mix beaten eggs, sugar and vinegar.
Smooth in the flour and cook over low heat, stirring until it thickens.
Add bacon fat.
Blend and cool.

title: coconut ice cream dessert
directions: Combine crackers and melted butter, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs. Pat remaining crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Let ice cream stand at room temperature for about 1/2 hour to soften. Add milk and pudding mix to ice cream and beat until smooth.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate to chill and set.
When ready to serve, spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup crumbs.
Tastes like good coconut cream pie!

title: easy chili ala jean mc
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with chopped or sliced onion. Do not overcook. Add tomato soup with 3/4 can water; stir. Add chili powder; stir.
(Use more if you desire.)
Add beans; stir.
Cover and simmer until 10 minutes are up. Serve over hamburger buns or in a bowl with a dollop of sour cream or cheese sprinkles. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: herbed pork
directions: Trim all visible fat. Puncture the chops with the tines of a fork at intervals of about 1/4 inch. Rub well with the cornstarch or flour. Place the tamari, herbs, garlic and pepper in a shallow bowl; marinate the chops for at least 2 hours (preferably overnight). Be sure the chops are coated on both sides with the marinade and turn 2 or 3 times. This marinade is an excellent tenderizer.

title: cinnamon-raisin coffeecake
directions: Combine half the nuts with the raisins, powdered sugar, margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Unroll breadsticks without separating.
Spread raisin mixture evenly over dough to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Fold in half lengthwise; seal long edges. Gently stretch dough to a 24-inch strip.
Twist slightly.
Shape into a circle on an ungreased baking sheet.
Seal ends.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 20 to 22 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly.
Drizzle with White Glaze.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Bring butter and milk to a boil.
Beat eggs and sugar until white in color.
Add vanilla and flour, then add the hot milk and butter.
Add baking powder.
Beat well.
Place a piece of waxed paper in bottom of angel food cake pan.
(I use Pam spray instead.)
Pour in mixture and bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pepper-onion relish
directions: Process onions and peppers, a few at a time, mixed with vinegar in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and boil until slightly thickened (about 45 minutes), stirring occasionally. Pack boiling hot into hot sterilized jars.
Seal and process in water bath for 5 minutes.
Good with vegetables or on hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers or square.
Stir together pudding mix and milk.
Add whipped topping; blend gently.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over graham crackers in pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press uncooked ground beef in bottom of large casserole dish. Chop onion and layer on top of beef.
Smooth soup on top of onion. Place sliced cheese on top of soup.
Layer Tater Tots on top; bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, or until bubbly in center.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: *Can substitute 1 can green string beans for broccoli or asparagus spears.

title: anise slices
directions: Add baking powder to warm milk.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Make into loaves on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Slice and brown under broiler.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Work together thoroughly.
Make into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; reduce to 325°, bake 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together	margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla, orange rind, milk and zucchini.	Mix with flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and
powdered	cocoa.	Stir,
don't beat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and stir well.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix and oil and cream batter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well and beat after each egg addition.
Add Jell-O to batter. Beat 1 minute.
Put in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan; remove.
While hot, pour glaze over cake.

title: bananas foster
directions: Scoop ice cream into a pasta bowl.
Slice banana.
In a small frying pan, melt butter into sugar, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add banana slices and cook for 2 or 3 minutes.
Splash in brandy, tipping the pan so that the brandy lights (be very careful that you don't burn off your eyebrows or hair).
Pour over ice cream and enjoy!

title: pumpkin carrot muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat together the brown sugar, oil, egg and pumpkin.
Add grated carrot.

title: tomato-onion salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: uncooked fondant
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl. Mix until creamy. Tint as desired with a few drops of food coloring. Drop small spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Decorate with nuts or candied fruit. Let stand to become firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup. Pour ketchup over top of loaf. Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: jello balls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 boxes Jell-O and other ingredients and chill for 2 hours.
Shape into balls and roll in Jell-O.
Let stand for 2 days.

title: c-foam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water until it threads.
Beat the egg whites with mixer until they are stiff.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Pour sugar and water mixture in eggs; mix until you can spoon it out.

title: pebbles mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done and chop.
Put chopped chicken in bottom of 9x13 casserole dish.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Add chopped onion.
Cover with sliced Velveeta cheese.	Crumble 1/2 bag nacho chips and layer over onions.
In separate bowl, mix soups and Rotel.
Pour over casserole.
Top with remaining crushed nacho chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp and catfish deep fry
directions: Peel, clean and butterfly shrimp.
Cut catfish fillets into large, bite size pieces.
Place shrimp and fish in large bowl. Stir in enough mustard to ensure all are well coated.
Stir in 1 tablespoon McCormick Season-All seasoning with 1 tablespoon of Tabasco.
Cover; let the seafood marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Bring peanut oil to frying temperature.
Dredge the shrimp and fish nuggets in fish fry; deep fry until golden brown.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients in order, except Marshmallow Creme. Spread in an 8-inch glass dish.
Cover with wax paper and bake in microwave oven for 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Spread Marshmallow Creme on top while warm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth with celery, carrots and onion (10 minutes).
Add all the rest of the ingredients.

title: grilled pot roast
directions: Poke holes in meat with fork.
Sprinkle with water and meat tenderizer.
Turn meat over and repeat process.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Mix soy sauce, Kitchen Bouquet, mustard and pepper.
Rub mixture on both sides of meat.
Grill over low to medium charcoal fire.
Turn meat after 45 minutes.
Grill another 45 minutes and remove.
Let stand a few minutes before carving.
Meat will be crusty on the outside.

title: jello-fruit cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake mix according to package directions, adding the cream cheese and lemon juice to filling mixture.
Chill until Jell-O mixture is ready to be poured over cheesecake mixture.

title: meringue
directions: Bring to boil; let cool before adding to egg whites (approximately 3). Add to beaten egg whites. Continue beating until stiff peaks form.

title: chunky hot sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes if you are not using diced tomatoes.
Add chopped onion and chopped peppers.
Cook until onion and peppers are soft.
Add cumin, garlic powder and chili powder; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour in jar or container.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine water and spaghetti sauce in large bowl.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, cover bottom with a thin layer of sauce.
Arrange dry, uncooked noodles.
Spread with Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Continue layers: sauce, noodles and cheese.
Completely cover noodles with sauce until all used up. Top with Mozzarella.

title: brownies
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Wash and separate broccoli into stems.
Cover and boil broccoli in 1 can of chicken broth for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Boil, covered.
Remove from broth, cool and chop coarsely. Add all ingredients to broth.
Add the other can of broth and heat to desired temperature, stirring often, until slightly thickened.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Place pieces of chicken in a 2-quart casserole.
Add water, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients.
Then mix together remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to dry mixture, stirring only enough to moisten dry mixture.
Turn into greased (bottom only) 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan or two small loaf pans and spread batter evenly to corners.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Cool 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Prepare jello by directions on box minus/cup was ???.
Let jello get heavy in the refrigerator.
After jello gets thick, mix in pineapple, strawberries and sliced bananas.
Divide jello and let 1/2 congeal.
After it congeals, put sour cream on top and sprinkle pecans.
Pour remaining jello over cream and nuts; congeal.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sour liver
directions: Cut liver into small pieces.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon fat until clear in appearance.
Add liver; stir frequently for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over meat mixture, stirring for 3 more minutes.
Add salt, pepper, paprika, water, wine, vinegar, bay leaf, clove and ginger berries; cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Goes well with noodles, rice and potatoes.

title: paprikash casserole
directions: Brown beef in 1 tablespoon oil in 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven until well browned.
Remove from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to drippings and cook onions and mushrooms until lightly browned. Stir in paprika and cook one minute.

title: roy's catfish stew
directions: Prepare fish in nuggets.
Cook fat back until done.
Add potatoes.
Cook until done; add onions.
Cook until done.
Pour in tomato catsup.
Add hot sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Add fish.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cook in salted water with skins for 10 to15 minutes.
Drain and peel.
Cut in half.
Put in buttered dish.
Rub with lemon juice.
Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Add butter to boiling water.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
No cover.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown the onion, green pepper and ground meat in the bacon fat.
Add the corn meal to 4 cups boiling salt water; cook in double boiler for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Simmer for about 10 minutes. Put half mush in buttered dish.
Add meat.
Cover with remaining mush.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 305° oven.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In bowl, mix all remaining ingredients except fruit filling.
Pour over margarine.
Do not mix together.
Spoon fruit over mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: veal marsala
directions: Saute garlic, veal, 1/8 cup of butter and 1/8 cup of water. Brown veal (no flour).
Saute mushrooms, 1/8 cup of butter, 1/8 cup of water and bouillon.
Mix mushrooms and veal.
Pour in the wine.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 400°.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Shape on platter (to look like a pie crust).
Spread thin layer of strawberry preserves on top and serve with Ritz or any cracker.
Very pretty, especially during the holidays.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top. Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes to an hour. This makes a pretty, brown cobbler.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in lo-cal Zesty
Italian dressing overnight.
Remove and place on a baking sheet for broiling or baking in oven.
No need for additional seasoning.
Turn about every 15 minutes until chicken is done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together. In another bowl, beat eggs, then fold into butter and sugar, then add molasses. In a very large pan, put all other ingredients, except the flour, and stir just to mix. Add the flour slowly into the mixture to coat the ingredients well. When all the fruit and nuts are covered with the flour, put this mixture into the liquids and blend well. Bake in a preheated 250° oven about 3 hours in 2 greased loaf pans or round tube pans. Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup sherry (optional, but good). Makes about 6 pounds.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased dish.
Refrigerate. Will be ready to eat in 1/2 hour.

title: oh! my pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until they are thick; cool completely.
Add bananas and chopped pecans.
This recipe will fill 3 pie crusts.
Refrigerate and top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top also.
Very rich!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin, eggs, oil and water. Add 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in greased and floured bread pan.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in cold water; slow heat.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Turn off and let set for 5 minutes in water.
Put a tablespoon of salt in water and let set for 5 more minutes so shells will not stick.
Peel eggs and cut in half long ways.
Mash and mix yellows with 2 tablespoons of Miracle Whip, 1 teaspoon of mustard and 1 tablespoon of chopped sweet pickles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fill eggs with yellow mix and sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: In a shallow dish, layer the ingredients in the following manner:

bean dip, avocados mashed with lemon juice mixed with mayonnaise, sour cream mixed with taco mix, onions (chopped fine), chopped olives, chopped tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese. Serve with 3 large bags Mexican chips.
Serves 20.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugars and oleo.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to the sugar and oleo mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut and rolled oats.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten a little.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: In medium bowl with fork, mix well first 6 ingredients.
Shape mixture into 12 large meatballs, placing a cube of cheese in the center of each and making sure that the cheese is covered.
On wax paper, coat each meatball lightly with flour.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; cool and add bananas and the juices.
Freeze.
Just before serving, let thaw until slushy, then add 7-Up.

title: gourmet onions
directions: Melt butter and stir in all ingredients except cheese.
Heat quickly, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rum baked bananas
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in buttered baking dish.
Brush bananas with lemon juice; sprinkle with rind and brown sugar.
Combine butter and rum; drizzle over bananas.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream.
Serves 2.

title: bacon cheese munchies(microwave)
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl.
Spread 1/2 the mixture on 12 Melba or other crackers.
Microwave on High for 30 to 60 seconds until heated.
Repeat with remaining mixture and crackers.

title: strawberry and cake dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Beat until fluffy.
Put frozen strawberries in blender and whip until thawed.
When strawberry jello mixture is syrupy, fold in cream cheese mixture.
Add strawberries.
Put this bowl in refrigerator until mixture is very thick.
Cut angel food cake in 3 layers.
Put strawberry mixture between layers.
Ice with whipped cream.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, oil, vinegar, eggs, food coloring and vanilla.
Mix together.
Bake in layer pans which have been greased and floured.
