Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rick mccabe's barbecue mopping sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer well before using. Great for basting smoked brisket, etc.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Melt shortening, add onion, garlic and meat.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 40 minutes.

title: uncle bobby's cake
directions: Poke fork holes all over the top of the cake.
Pour butterscotch sauce over cake; let it soak in.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Sprinkle with crushed candy bars.

title: oven stew for 60
directions: I make 3 times the recipe.

title: josephinas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 425° until cheese bubbles.
Serve hot as appetizer.

title: barbecued party franks
directions: Cut wieners in 1-inch lengths.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over wieners.
Marinate overnight.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Cover with brown gravy and cook over open fire in a huge pot for about 4 weeks at 425°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, two rabbits may be added, only do that if necessary because most people do not like to find hare in their food.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix & put in casserole dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers - dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 30 min. till bubbly & brown on top.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce, broth, water, celery, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables.
Return to boil.
Cover.
Simmer 10 more minutes.

title: dorothy's chili con carne
directions: Clean frog legs thoroughly with running cold water.
Sprinkle legs with Cajun seasoning first, then black pepper, then very lightly with red pepper.
Coat legs in flour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, egg yolk, onion, salt and sugar.
Stir in Bisquick mix.
Beat egg whites in separate bowl and fold into corn batter. Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep oil in large frypan and cook until golden brown.
Or fry as patties using smaller amount of oil. Makes about 15 fritters.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, vanilla and sugar gradually.
Add milk until fluffy; beat in egg.
Mix flavoring, baking powder and soda with milk alternately.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Let dissolve.
After ingredients have dissolved, add to other ingredients.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Soak raisins in hot water, drain.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and butter.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix just until moistened.
Don't overmix.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for one hour.

title: papaya smoothie
directions: In blender, puree papaya and banana.
Add ice cubes and blend. Fold in yogurt.
Pour into stemmed glasses.

title: nut cake
directions: First melt butter. Add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Mix in flour, one cup at a time.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Use a large pan as this makes a big cake.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Cool in pan.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground beef with bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 can tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper. Form into loaf. Place in shallow pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Combine 1/2 can tomato sauce, water, mustard and sugar. Pour over meat loaf, basting occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine other ingredients except the butter. In a baking dish, place melted butter in bottom and pour corn mixture over this.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife inserted in mixture comes out clean.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small, bite size pieces.
It is best to start this well in advance of the anticipated company.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Simmer over a kerosene fire for about 4 weeks or until tender.
This will serve 3,839 people (if they are not gluttons).
If more guests are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added.

title: sugar-cinnamon cookies
directions: *Make sour milk by adding 1 tablespoon vinegar; let set 2 or 3 minutes.

title: cranberry orange chicken
directions: In a large frying pan, melt butter. Add chicken and cook about 10 minutes on each side.

In medium size nonaluminum saucepan, combine orange juice, cranberries, honey, orange peel, cornstarch and cloves. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened. Spoon sauce over chicken breasts.

title: butterscotch noodle clusters(candy)
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels on low heat.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill.

title: mexican dip(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all together.
Put in crock-pot on low.
Serve hot.

title: beer batter shrimp
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine beer and egg and pour over mixture; mix well.	Dip shrimp in batter and deep fry in hot peanut oil; cook until golden brown.

title: grecian chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cut a pocket into each chicken breast; salt & pepper to taste; set aside.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring often.
Separate biscuits in half, forming 2 rounds; cut each round in half.
Drop biscuit pieces, 1 at a time, into boiling mixture; stir gently.
Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raised donuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Mix all remaining ingredients. Let rise.
Poke down and cut out.
Let rise again.
Fry.
Eat warm with warm pure maple syrup.
Yes, 2 cups water is correct.

title: cherry pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small cup, mix together the 3 extracts. Spray a 13 x 9 baking pan with Pam baking spray. In a large bowl, stir together the cherry pie filling, pineapple and extract mixture. Pour mixture evenly into the baking pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly across the top of the mixture. Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pat's rice custard
directions: Mix milk, rice, sugar, salt and raisins.
Cook in double boiler until rice is cooked.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and nutmeg.

title: creamy holiday fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate, stirring occasionally.
Add milk, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Spread mixture in wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours until firm. Turn onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares. Tightly cover leftovers.

title: walnut jam crescents(no sugar)
directions: Combine flour with salt.
Cut in butter until fine particles. Add sour cream and mix to a stiff dough.
Divide into 2 even-size portions.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Chop walnuts fine.
Roll each portion to an 11-inch round.
Spread with 1/2 cup jam and sprinkle with nuts.
Cut in quarters, then each quarter into 3 wedges.
Roll up one at a time, starting from outer edge, and place on lightly greased sheet.
Repeat with second pastry round.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage, biscuits and gravy
directions: Brown sausage in pan; season as desired.
Add whole milk and bring to a boil.
Blend 12 ounces milk with flour to thicken. Pour this over boiling milk and sausage.
Bring to boil again and simmer until thickened.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Beat all these ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Mixture will be very watery.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Cake will be very moist.

title: chicken 'n biscuit
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Roll biscuits as thin as possible on waxed paper.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan, pressing dough together at seams.
Spread chicken mixture down center of dough and overlap the dough over the mixture to form a loaf.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
While baking, heat soup and milk and pour over crust.
Continue baking 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve hot.

title: pepper relish
directions: Take seeds out of peppers and then put through food processor with onions.
Boil the water and then pour over the pepper and onion mixture.
Let this stand until cool.
Use cheesecloth to squeeze out water. Boil the vinegar and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Pour over the peppers and cook for 20 minutes.
Seal while hot in canning jars.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with eggs and sour cream.
Add flavoring.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: tuna and shell salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, hot sauce, celery, onions and bell pepper.
Add tuna fish and macaroni.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: boy scout hamburgers
directions: Make a cake of hamburg as big as desired.
Cover with sliced raw potatoes and sliced carrots; add cut up onion also.
Wrap in foil, if desired, to bake, or put in a baking dish.
Salt to taste.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: *If desired, substitute 1 bag (16 ounces) any frozen vegetable combination, cooked and drained, for fresh vegetables.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken. Remove from skin and bones.
Prepare rice according to directions on box. Cut chicken into pieces and add mushrooms 5 to 10 minutes before rice is done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: If fresh peas and carrots are used, saute with onion.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare 1/2 of pastry and fit into 9-inch pie pan. Melt butter over low heat; blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and veggies and pour into pie pan.
Place second crust over top.
Pinch edges together and make slits in crust.
Cover edge with strip of foil to prevent overbrowning.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cut into medium pieces. Add onions and eggs. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Slice bananas; put on top.
Drain pineapple; put on top of bananas.
Spread on whipped cream.
Top with cherries and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Cool.

title: cookies
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to boil (take off heat). Add peanut butter and Special K cereal. Stir and drop on cookie sheet.

title: pimento sandwich spread
directions: Mix cheese, vinegar, sugar, flour and eggs.
Heat over low heat.
Stir continually until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add pimento.
Store in covered jar.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: About 8 hours before serving, mash bananas until smooth in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well combined. Pour mixture into a 9 x 9-inch flat pan or dish, not metal. Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until partially frozen, about 2 hours.
Spoon mixture into a large chilled bowl. With mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth but still frozen. Return mixture to pan. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: caramel pecan candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook until medium to hard boiled stage when dropped in cool water.
Remove from heat and add butter and then pecans.
Beat and drop on cookie sheet until it hardens.

title: crabmeat dip or spread
directions: Mix well.
Let chill.
Serve with seafood cocktail sauce on crackers or vegetables.

title: fish (striper) casserole
directions: Saute the onions and celery in the olive oil.
Line a baking dish with the onions and celery.
Mix a box of Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Put a thin layer of dressing over onions and celery. Next, you put a layer of fish, a layer of dressing and keep building with fish and dressing, making the last layer or top dressing.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: shanghai salad
directions: Place all ingredients, except almonds, in a large bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over all and toss well.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 15 servings.

title: senate bean soup
directions: In large saucepot or Dutch oven, soak beans overnight in 6 cups water (or bring to boil; boil 2 minutes and let stand, covered 1 hour).
Add remaining 4 cups water, the ham hock, bay leaf and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 1/4 hours or until beans are almost tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes more until beans are tender. Discard bay leaf.
Cut meat from bones and return to soup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours). Cool.
Save broth.
Make stuffing according to package directions, but use 2 cups broth.
Mix soups together with 1 cup broth.
Cook broccoli pieces slightly in water and drain.

title: elaine's chicken and black bean enchiladas
directions: Simmer all but onions and tortillas for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add onions and spoon mixture into tortilla.
Spoon additional picante evenly over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese and return to oven for about 3 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce and sour cream.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook pasta in oil and salt. Brown hamburger. Add ingredients.

title: ernie's sausage quiche
directions: *You may substitute ingredients of your choice, such as bacon, Swiss cheese, Egg Beaters and skim milk.

title: vegetable soup(low fat - no cholesterol)
directions: Put tomatoes, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cook until done. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until zucchini is tender.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan and heat until boiling.
Let cool.

title: kitty's plum bread
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In a bowl, beat together the eggs, oil, milk and liqueur, then add the plums. Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Line 2 loaf pans with foil.
Spray foil with Pam.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from oven and pour glaze on top while still warm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables with onion; drain.
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese mixture.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing (dry).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(Dressing may be placed on bottom layer, if desired.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Place meat in bowl, add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack the mixture in a 1 1/2-quart loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven on lower rack for 1 hour.
Pour off any fat that may have accumulated.
Serve hot or cold.
Mixture can be divided into 6 cups of a muffin tin.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out bread to 10-inch round.
Mix egg and Parmesan cheese. Spread over bread.
Chop pepperoni in little pieces.
Sprinkle over bread.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over pepperoni.
Roll up into a loaf.
Pinch ends together.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until thick and pale.
Gradually add sugar, beating until blended.
Add oil and vanilla; beat at low until blended.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to beaten mixture.
Stir until blended.
Stir in apples and pecans. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in cake pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift cake flour; add to mixture.
Add 7-Up soda.
Beat batter until fluffy.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Toss the cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over the top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppin fresh barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides, forming 1/4 inch rim.
Spoon 1/4 cup meat mixture into each cup. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove from pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Put fruit into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt margarine and pour over mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower-cheese soup
directions: Cook and stir cauliflower in butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until crisp and tender, about 6 minutes.
Stir in water, cheese, half and half, instant bouillon and allspice.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in wine; heat about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle green pepper and paprika over soup. Serve with warm breadsticks.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound seasoned flour into sides of the steak.
Brown pounded steak in hot fat in a heavy skillet.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat or in a moderate 300° oven until tender (2 to 2 1/2 hours), uncovering the last 1/2 hour to cook down sauce to a rich thickness.
Serve hot.

title: ragout of veal
directions: *Can substitute pork or lamb.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom.
Mix cake mix as to directions on box.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: light crab spread
directions: Finely chop onion.
Press garlic through a garlic press.
Mix onion, garlic, cream cheese and milk until well blended.
Spread on small plate or tray.

title: beef and onions
directions: In large skillet, cook meat, mushrooms, onions and garlic until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain off fat. Mix beef gravy, yogurt, Worcestershire sauce, sage and pepper. Add to meat mixture and heat until hot.
Serve over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: bubble and squeak(english recipe)
directions: In large frypan melt butter.
Cut up cabbage.
Put into pan with mashed potatoes.
Saute until brown and crispy.
Serve with almost anything.
Good with ham, bacon and vegetables.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream and salsa; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch glass pie plate; cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 5 minutes; stir.
Microwave 4 minutes or until center is no longer wet.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately with salsa and sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Divide into 4 balls and roll into logs.
Chill and slice 1/2-inch thick. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Better if chilled overnight.)

title: cream of mushroom chicken
directions: Brown chicken parts in a frying pan.
Season with lemon and herb seasoning and pepper.
Place chicken pieces in a baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk together and pour over chicken.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add Cool Whip, pudding mix and milk.
Mix well and pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: jicama coleslaw
directions: Thoroughly combine all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Refrigerate before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato filling
directions: Make mashed potatoes (either instant or regular). Add a good handful of bread cubes.
Then add seasonings (parsley flakes, onion and garlic salt and pepper).
No special measurements. Just add to taste.
Either serve as is or bake in oven with pats of butter on top.
Bake until brown.

title: pork chop casserole for two
directions: Brown pork chops in margarine until brown.
Remove from pan. In the same pan, brown onion and remove.
Slice potatoes and brown in same pan.
Melt bouillon cube in hot water.

title: green tomato wine
directions: Grind or chop tomatoes.
Pour boiling water on raisins and let soak for 10 minutes; drain, saving water.
Add enough to make 3 3/4 quarts (part barley water will result in wine with more body). Bring water to boil and dissolve sugar in it.
Add tomatoes, raisins and oranges.
When cooled to lukewarm, add wine yeast, softened as directed on package.
Stir in yeast nutrient and tea. Cover top of 3 gallon fermenting vessel with cheesecloth or clean towel tied down after mixture is added.
Keep in warm place for 3 days, stirring twice a day.
Siphon into clean gallon jug, straining out fruit; fit with airlock.
Keep in warm place until all signs of fermentation have ceased.
Rack off into clean gallon jug.
Fit with airlock again.
Keep in cool place until wine clears.
Rack off again and bottle.
I have not tried this one, but it sounds enchanting!

title: salmon biscuit ring
directions: Lay the crescent rolls on a cookie sheet and press into 1 piece.
Drain and flaked the salmon.
Combine with egg, cheese, onions and parsley; mix well.
Spread salmon mixture to about 1-inch from longest side.
Roll into a roll and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: old fashioned peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy, gradually adding sugar and remaining ingredients.
Add milk to fill.
Makes one gallon of delicious peach ice cream.

title: snappy cheese
directions: Grind cheese with garlic.
Add salt and Tabasco to taste. Add stale beer to desired consistency. Let sit out in open container for 24 hours. Cover and refrigerate.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream with butter both sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Add chips, chocolate bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together in saucepan the sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When this mixture comes to a boil, boil exactly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: colvin's spuds
directions: Place ingredients in pan covered with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening and 1 cup of the flour, stirring until smooth.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Stir down batter. Spoon into 12 muffin cups, about 1/2 full.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling point.
Pour over flour and sugar, beating well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix again.
Bake in greased and floured sheet pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Simple, but delicious!

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Start with top ingredient and continue as listed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into squares when cool.

title: poor man's pudding
directions: Melt down margarine in frypan. Add graham cracker crumbs; stir until crumbs get slightly brown.
Put aside to cool.

title: black bottoms
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, beaten egg and salt and beat.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; batter will be thin.
Beat well.
Fill cupcake cups 1/3 full of this mixture.
Drop spoonful of chocolate chip mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Mix hot water in jello.
Add the juice of the crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir really well.
Jell until almost firm.
Take from refrigerator and use mixer to beat jello until really foamy.
Add jello to rest of ingredients a little at a time.
It will be very thick.
Let jell or it can be frozen.

title: mandarin poppy seed salad
directions: Tear lettuce up into bowl.
Slice red onion and put onion (sliced into rings) into bowl.
Drain mandarin oranges and put into bowl.
Place in frige until 15 minutes before eating.
Add almonds and poppy seed dressing.
Toss thoroughly.
Fast and delicious!

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Use an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond bark mix
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Mix in other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Marinate 2 to 3 pounds of chicken overnight in lemon, oil and spices.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, basting often with marinade.

title: mother's southern cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Put on cookie sheet by the spoonful; press down and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked plums
directions: Remove pits from plums and place in an 8-cup baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, except the 10x sugar, in a blender. Blend until smooth.
Pour batter over plums and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Coat surface with 10x sugar (sifted) and reheat.
This can be made with cherries, peaches, apples and other fruits.
Also good served with whipped cream.

title: pea and macaroni salad
directions: Boil your macaroni until tender and drain.
Run cold water over macaroni to stop cooking process.
After fully drained, add your sweet peas from the can, drained.
Add onion and mayonnaise to the peas and macaroni mixture.
Stir gently and refrigerate overnight.
Great for brunches!!!

title: sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Form meatballs (approximately 40), using the first 4 ingredients.
Next, mix together the sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce, water and brown sugar.
Pour 1/2 of the sauerkraut mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan, then a layer of meatballs, then the remainder of the sauerkraut mixture.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 325°, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in 9 x 13 greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Freezes well. In muffin tin, bake less time!

title: steamed chinese broccoli with oyster sauce
directions: Steam broccoli 4 to 6 minutes just until tender.
Mix oyster sauce, sugar, chicken stock and wine.
Heat in a sauce pan and add peanut oil.
When hot, add garlic and stir briefly.
Add oyster sauce and bring to a boil.	Stir cornstarch and water together and add oyster sauce.
When sauce thickens, turn off heat and drizzle sesame oil over it.
Pour sauce over broccoli and serve.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually mix in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Roll small balls in coconut.
Store in sealed containers in cool place.
Yield:
about 80 walnut size balls.

title: raw mountain relish
directions: Chop vegetables and mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight.
Pack in boiling hot jars and seal.
No cooking at all. Very good on hot dogs as well as dried beans.

title: sweet potato casserole(for 12)
directions: Potatoes
may
be
boiled or cooked carefully in microwave; skin.
(May
be
done earlier.) Prepare in a Mixmaster. Put in greased casserole.	(May be frozen at this point.) When ready
to serve, heat thoroughly in 300° oven.
Put small dabs of
oleo. Sprinkle cinnamon.	Add small marshmallows to cover top before putting in oven.
Prepare 1/2 cup per person.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in pizza sauce, undrained mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to boiling and then remove from heat.
Combine rotini and milk.
In 2-quart casserole layer 1/2 of each of the meat sauce, rotini mixture and cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.
Garnish with salami slices, cherry tomatoes and parsley.

title: grilled oriental steak
directions: Blend spices in a closeable container.
Place steaks in.
Blend and brush over meat.
Refrigerate overnight to marinate.
Preheat gas grill to high, then add steaks to sear outside.
Flip over; continue cooking until your desired doneness.

title: cream cheese bridge sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese with enough mayonnaise to soften.
Combine all ingredients and spread on small squares or bridge cut-outs of pumpernickel bread.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine and pat into greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli and ham soup
directions: In a 3 qt. glass microwave-safe casserole, combine onion, garlic and butter or margarine.
Microcook at high for 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in ham, broth, broccoli, undrained tomatoes, water, macaroni and nutmeg.
Cover and cook at high for 15 minutes or until boiling, stirring once to break up broccoli. Continue cooking on medium for 8 minutes or until broccoli and macaroni are tender.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 6 servings each with 193 calories, 12 g. fat and 20 mg. cholesterol.

title: cheese salad
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly so it won't burn.
Refrigerate until it is almost set; whip until foamy.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Blend together.
Add the grated cheese.
Cool.

title: easy cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Place ham and cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy salted nut roll
directions: Put half of the peanuts in 9 x 13 greased pan. Melt together the peanut butter chips and butter. Add the milk. Stir in the marshmallows. Don't let the marshmallows melt. Pour over peanuts; press down. Put remaining peanuts on top and press down.

title: baked onion
directions: Wash and peel onion.
Remove center core of onion.
Fill opening with margarine and bouillon cube.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a cookie sheet for 30 to 45 minutes, until onion is tender.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Mix the syrup and sugars together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the peanut butter and let it melt.
Add the corn flakes.
Put into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the top.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Measure together flour, baking soda and salt; sift and set aside.
Work butter with fork until soft, gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately blending well.
Stir in pecans, dates and raisins.
Grease 9-inch tube pan, line bottom with aluminum foil and grease again.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes or until done.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Cut chicken off bones into bite-size pieces.
Saute in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, on top of range about 20 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: peppermint cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flavoring.
Mix flour and salt.
Stir in together.
Chill overnight.
Form into cookies.

title: spiced percolator punch
directions: Put spices in basket of coffeepot.
Into bottom of coffeepot, put juices, water and brown sugar and perk as you would coffee. Serve hot.

title: marinated raw mushrooms
directions: Cut the stems from the mushrooms and reserve.
Cut the ends from the stems.
Wash the mushrooms thoroughly; dry and slice. Mix the remaining ingredients together and add the mushroom tips and stems; toss until all the pieces are coated.
Let stand at room temperature for several hours before serving.
Serve with picks as a cocktail accompaniment.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Mix in Crisco until it resembles coarse meal.
Pack in a covered container.
I use Tupperware canister. Doesn't need to be refrigerated.

title: layered salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer ingredients in order given.
After layer of peas, spread mayonnaise over top to seal.
Sift Parmesan cheese over mayonnaise. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, add sliced eggs and bacon (crumbled). Toss to blend.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust and chill until set, approximately 4 hours. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: burger beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain.
Add beef mixture with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a large Pyrex dish for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut steaks into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix lime juice, oil, tequila and spices.
Pour over meat.
Marinate 4 hours, turning often.
Grill meat 5 to 10 minutes each side.
Slice meat against grain in 1/4-inch strips.
Place meat in warm tortillas and garnish as desired.
Roll up to eat.
Garnish with salsa, guacamole, cilantro or sour cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream sugars and melted butter.
Add flour, cocoa, milk, vanilla and eggs; mix until smooth, then stir in nuts.
Pour into crust.
Bake for about 55 minutes at 325°.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a greased dish or pan.
Place a slice of cheese on each breast.
Mix soup with 1/2 can of liquor and pour over chicken.
Melt stick of butter and toss in 1/2 bag of stuffing.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil, then another 1/2 hour without foil.
If more liquid is needed, add milk or liquor.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl combine sausage, Bisquick, milk and cheese. Knead ingredients together to form soft dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice up potatoes.
Add enough water to cover.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add celery, onion and butter.
Add bacon or sausage.
Also add parsley.
Cook until almost all the water is gone.
Then cover with milk.
Simmer until done.
Do not boil.
So good on a cold winter day!

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add rice and tomato sauce.
Add water, enough to cover rice, about an inch.
Add seasonings to taste.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Leave uncovered and cook until liquid is almost gone.
Lower heat for the last few minutes to dry out the rice.
Be careful not to burn it.
Serves 4.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and form into balls.
Bake, uncovered, in single layer in large pan for 30 to 45 minutes until brown and done.
Heat 1 can consomme with 1 can of water.
Add to cooked meatballs and serve.

title: turkey-green beans parmesan
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions; drain (or use canned green French-style beans).
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat. Fold in mayonnaise, lemon peel and juice.
Stir in turkey. Spread green beans in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Pour in turkey sauce mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken alfred
directions: Drain marinade from artichoke hearts into large skillet and add olive oil.
Dredge chicken in flour and parsley and brown in oil until golden.
Transfer chicken pieces to a large casserole dish.
Combine tomatoes and artichoke hearts in the pan the chicken was fried in.
Add spices and mushrooms; simmer until all is hot, then pour over chicken, cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Add sherry wine.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: lemon delight pound cake
directions: While mixing on high, grease Bundt pan good.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix juice of 1 lemon with powdered sugar to thick (not too) consistency.
Let cake rest 20 minutes, then turn out.
Ice immediately.

title: candied apples
directions: Either	core or quarter apples.
Put in a baking pan or casserole dish
and
sprinkle
strawberry
jello and pieces of small red hot candies over apples.	Add sugar and water.
Cook slowly in moderate oven.

title: german pancakes
directions: Beat 5 minutes in all.
Beat eggs lightly.
Beat in the sifted flour, salt, sugar, milk, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Melt enough butter in a wide frying pan to coat bottom.
When hot, pour 4 to 5 tablespoons of batter in pan.
Make batter spread to form a large, thin flat pancake.
Cook until batter bubbles.
Turn and bake the other side.
Slip onto hot plate.
Serve with small amount of jelly or syrup.
Be careful not to use too much sweets as the pancakes have a delicious flavor of their own.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and egg; mix well.
Add milk and stir until flour disappears.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove from skillet and pour off fat.
Add potatoes, pepper and onion to skillet.
Cook until lightly browned.
Pour eggs over potatoes.
Cover and cook until eggs are suitably firm.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese. Cover and heat until cheese melts.

title: mable cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press mixture onto bottom and 1/2-inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool; set aside.
